{"title_page": "International Commission of Control and Supervision", "text_new": "[[File:1973 Vietnam Vinh Long ICCS.jpg|thumb]]\n{{distinguish|International Control Commission|International Commission of Control}}\nThe '''International Commission of Control and Supervision''' (ICCS) was created during the [[Vietnam War]] to replace the [[International Control Commission]] (formally called the International Commission for Supervision and Control in Vietnam (ICSC)) following the signing of the [[Paris Peace Accords]] (\"Paris Agreement on Ending the War and Restoring Peace in Vietnam\") on 27 January 1973.\n\nThe Protocol to the Paris Agreement detailed the functions of the ICCS. At Article 4 it named the locations of seven regional teams and twenty-six teams within those regions in [[South Vietnam]]. It also called for seven teams to be assigned to ports of entry (for replacement of armaments, munitions and war material permitted the two South Vietnamese parties under Article 7 of the Agreement) and seven teams to supervise the return of captured and detained personnel.\n\nIn summary, the ICCS was to supervise the cease-fire, the withdrawal of troops, the dismantlement of military bases, the activity at ports of entry and the return of captured military personnel and foreign civilians. It was to report on the implementation, or violation, of the Peace Agreement and Protocols. The force was composed of military and civilian personnel from two communist nations, Hungary and Poland, and two non-communist nations, Canada and Indonesia. As with the old ICSC, there were continuous disagreements between the [[communist]] and non-communist nations about the causes of treaty violations. Canada attempted to counter this with an \"open mouth policy\" to the world's media.\n\n[[Canada]] remained a member of the ICCS from 29 January until 31 July 1973. During this period there were 18,000 alleged cease-fire violations, which resulted in over 76,000 killed, wounded and missing to both sides. On 7 April 1973 one Canadian (Captain Charles Laviolette of the 12<sup>e</sup> Regiment blind\u00e9 du Canada) and eight others from [[People's Republic of Hungary|Hungary]] (2 people: border guard Captain Aur\u00e9l Dylski and 1st Lt Csaba Cziboly), [[Indonesia]], the [[Philippines]], [[People's Republic of Poland|Poland]], and the [[United States]] were killed on 7 April 1973 when an ICCS helicopter operated by [[Air America (airline)|Air America]] was shot down by a [[People's Army of Vietnam]] [[9K32 Strela-2|SA-7 missile]] near [[National Route 9 (Vietnam)|Route 9]] in [[Qu\u1ea3ng Tr\u1ecb Province]].<ref name=LeGro>{{cite book|last=Le Gro|first=William|title=Vietnam from ceasefire to capitulation|publisher=US Army Center of Military History|year=1985|isbn=9781410225429|url=https://history.army.mil/html/books/090/90-29/CMH_Pub_90-29.pdf|page=36}}</ref> This was the only Canadian fatality during its time with the ICCS. On 29 May 1973 the Canadians announced that they were withdrawing from the ICCS because they had come to supervise a ceasefire but instead were observing a war.<ref name=LeGro/>{{rp|50}} After Canada's departure from the Commission, it was replaced by [[Iran]].\n\nPersonnel who served at least 90 days with the ICCS were awarded the [[International Commission of Control and Supervision Medal]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.jstor.org/pss/2199477 Protocol Concerning the International Commission of Control and Supervision. The American Journal of International Law, Vol. 67, No. 2 (Apr., 1973), pp. 412-418]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20160305233124/http://acc-vac.gc.ca/remembers/sub.cfm?source=collections%2Fcmdp%2Fmainmenu%2Fgroup06%2Ficmvn  International Commission of Control and Supervision Vietnam 1973 - ICCS (Operation Gallant)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110721113839/http://www.vietnamihaboru.hu/tanulmany/delusion-or-reality_-secret-hungarian-diplomacy-during-the-vietnam-war Hungarian involvement in Vietnam (1962-1975)]\n\n[[Category:Intergovernmental organizations established by treaty]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of Canada]]\n[[Category:Vietnam War]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1973]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|International Control Commission|International Commission of Control}}\nThe '''International Commission of Control and Supervision''' (ICCS) was created during the [[Vietnam War]] to replace the [[International Control Commission]] (formally called the International Commission for Supervision and Control in Vietnam (ICSC)) following the signing of the [[Paris Peace Accords]] (\"Paris Agreement on Ending the War and Restoring Peace in Vietnam\") on 27 January 1973.\n\nThe Protocol to the Paris Agreement detailed the functions of the ICCS. At Article 4 it named the locations of seven regional teams and twenty-six teams within those regions in [[South Vietnam]]. It also called for seven teams to be assigned to ports of entry (for replacement of armaments, munitions and war material permitted the two South Vietnamese parties under Article 7 of the Agreement) and seven teams to supervise the return of captured and detained personnel.\n\nIn summary, the ICCS was to supervise the cease-fire, the withdrawal of troops, the dismantlement of military bases, the activity at ports of entry and the return of captured military personnel and foreign civilians. It was to report on the implementation, or violation, of the Peace Agreement and Protocols. The force was composed of military and civilian personnel from two communist nations, Hungary and Poland, and two non-communist nations, Canada and Indonesia. As with the old ICSC, there were continuous disagreements between the [[communist]] and non-communist nations about the causes of treaty violations. Canada attempted to counter this with an \"open mouth policy\" to the world's media.\n\n[[Canada]] remained a member of the ICCS from 29 January until 31 July 1973. During this period there were 18,000 alleged cease-fire violations, which resulted in over 76,000 killed, wounded and missing to both sides. On 7 April 1973 one Canadian (Captain Charles Laviolette of the 12<sup>e</sup> Regiment blind\u00e9 du Canada) and eight others from [[People's Republic of Hungary|Hungary]] (2 people: border guard Captain Aur\u00e9l Dylski and 1st Lt Csaba Cziboly), [[Indonesia]], the [[Philippines]], [[People's Republic of Poland|Poland]], and the [[United States]] were killed on 7 April 1973 when an ICCS helicopter operated by [[Air America (airline)|Air America]] was shot down by a [[People's Army of Vietnam]] [[9K32 Strela-2|SA-7 missile]] near [[National Route 9 (Vietnam)|Route 9]] in [[Qu\u1ea3ng Tr\u1ecb Province]].<ref name=LeGro>{{cite book|last=Le Gro|first=William|title=Vietnam from ceasefire to capitulation|publisher=US Army Center of Military History|year=1985|isbn=9781410225429|url=https://history.army.mil/html/books/090/90-29/CMH_Pub_90-29.pdf|page=36}}</ref> This was the only Canadian fatality during its time with the ICCS. On 29 May 1973 the Canadians announced that they were withdrawing from the ICCS because they had come to supervise a ceasefire but instead were observing a war.<ref name=LeGro/>{{rp|50}} After Canada's departure from the Commission, it was replaced by [[Iran]].\n\nPersonnel who served at least 90 days with the ICCS were awarded the [[International Commission of Control and Supervision Medal]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.jstor.org/pss/2199477 Protocol Concerning the International Commission of Control and Supervision. The American Journal of International Law, Vol. 67, No. 2 (Apr., 1973), pp. 412-418]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20160305233124/http://acc-vac.gc.ca/remembers/sub.cfm?source=collections%2Fcmdp%2Fmainmenu%2Fgroup06%2Ficmvn  International Commission of Control and Supervision Vietnam 1973 - ICCS (Operation Gallant)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110721113839/http://www.vietnamihaboru.hu/tanulmany/delusion-or-reality_-secret-hungarian-diplomacy-during-the-vietnam-war Hungarian involvement in Vietnam (1962-1975)]\n\n[[Category:Intergovernmental organizations established by treaty]]\n[[Category:Foreign relations of Canada]]\n[[Category:Vietnam War]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1973]]\n", "name_user": "Inga k k", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Commission_of_Control_and_Supervision"}
{"title_page": "Calystegia", "text_new": "{{automatic taxobox\n|image = Calystegia sepium ssp sepium bluete.jpeg\n|image_caption = ''[[Calystegia sepium]]''\n|image2 = Calystegia soldanella 060524wb.jpg\n|image2_caption = ''[[Calystegia soldanella]]''\n|taxon = Calystegia\n|authority = [[Robert Brown (botanist, born 1773)|R.Br.]]<ref name=IPNI/><ref name=Brown/>\n|subdivision_ranks = Species\n|subdivision = See text\n}}\n\n'''''Calystegia''''' ('''bindweed''', '''false bindweed''', or '''morning glory''') is a genus of about 25 species of [[angiosperms|flowering plant]]s in the bindweed family [[Convolvulaceae]]. The genus has a [[cosmopolitan distribution]] in temperate and subtropical regions, but with half of the species [[endemic (ecology)|endemic]] to [[California]].  They are [[annual plant|annual]] or [[herbaceous]] [[perennial plant|perennial]] twining [[vine]]s growing 1\u20135&nbsp;m tall, with spirally arranged leaves. The [[flower]]s are trumpet-shaped, 3\u201310&nbsp;cm diameter, white or pink, with a sometimes inflated basal epicalyx.\n\nThe genus bears much similarity to a related genus ''[[Convolvulus]]'', and is sometimes combined with it; it is distinguished primarily by the [[pollen]] being smooth, and in the [[ovary (plants)|ovary]] being [[Locule|unilocular]].\n\nSome of the species, notably ''[[Calystegia sepium]]'' and ''[[Calystegia silvatica|C. silvatica]]'', are problematic [[weed]]s, which can swamp other more valuable plants by climbing over them, but some are also deliberately grown for their attractive [[flower]]s.\n\n''Calystegia'' species are used as food plants by the [[larva]]e of some [[Lepidoptera]] species including ''[[Bedellia somnulentella]]'' (recorded on ''C. sepium'') and [[small angle shades]].\n\nThe name is derived from two Greek words ''kalux'', \"cup\", and ''stege'', \"a covering\", meaning \"a covering cup\". <ref> [https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/Calystegia].: Merriam-Webster dictionary:Calystegia] </ref>\n\n==Species==\nThe following species are recognised in the genus ''Calystegia'':<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://powo.science.kew.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:331450-2|title=Calystegia R.Br. {{!}} Plants of the World Online {{!}} Kew Science|website=Plants of the World Online|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n*''[[Calystegia affinis]]''\n*''[[Calystegia atriplicifolia]]'' \u2013 nightblooming false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia binghamiae]]'' \n*''[[Calystegia brummittii]]''\n*''[[Calystegia catesbiana]]'' \u2013 Catesby's false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia collina]]'' \u2013 Coast Range false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia felix]]''\n*''[[Calystegia hederacea]]'' \u2013 Japanese false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 howittiorum]]''\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 krauseana]]''\n*''[[Calystegia longipes]]'' \u2013 Paiute false bindweed, plateau morning glory \n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 lucana]]''\n*''[[Calystegia macaunii]]'' \u2013  Macoun's false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia macrostegia]]'' \u2013 island false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia malacophylla]]'' \u2013  sierra false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia marginata]]'' \u2013 small-flowered white bindweed New Zealand<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nzpcn.org.nz/flora_details.aspx?ID=229|title=Calystegia marginata {{!}} New Zealand Plant Conservation Network|website=www.nzpcn.org.nz|access-date=2018-12-10}}</ref>\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 melnikovae]]''\n*''[[Calystegia occidentalis]]'' \u2013 chaparral false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia peirsonii]]'' \u2013 Peirson's false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia pellita]]'' \u2013 hairy false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia pubescens]]\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 pulchra]]'' \u2013 hairy bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia purpurata]]'' \u2013 Pacific false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 scania]]''\n*''[[Calystegia sepium]]'' \u2013 large bindweed, hedge bindweed, bearbind, hedgebell ([[type species]]) \n*''[[Calystegia silvatica]]'' \u2013 great bindweed, shortstalk bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia soldanella]]'' \u2013 sea bindweed, seashore false bindweed, beach morning glory\n*''[[Calystegia spithamaea]]'' \u2013 low false bindweed, upright bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia stebbinsii]]'' \u2013 Stebbins' false bindweed, Stebbins' morning glory\n*''[[Calystegia subacaulis]]'' \u2013 hillside false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia tuguriorium|Calystegia tuguriorum]]'' \u2013 New Zealand bindweed, p\u014duwhiwhi, p\u014dwhiwhi, rarotawake<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nzpcn.org.nz/flora_details.aspx?ID=1582|title=Calystegia tuguriorum {{!}} New Zealand Plant Conservation Network|website=www.nzpcn.org.nz|access-date=2018-12-10}}</ref>[[File:P\u014duwhiwhi_(Calystegia_tuguriorum).jpg|thumb|New Zealand bindweed]]\n*''[[Calystegia vanzuukiae]]''\n\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"200px\">\nFile:DSCM1934_Helix_Zaunwinde.jpg\nFile:Flore des serres et des jardins de l'Europe (8595873042).jpg|''[[Calystegia sepium]]'' ([[Louis van Houtte|van Houtte, L.]], 1853)\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=IPNI>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=331450-2 |title=Convolvulaceae ''Calystegia'' R.Br. The International Plant Name Index (IPNI)|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=Brown> Brown, R. (1810) {{cite web|url=https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/36315760|title=Prodromus flor\u00e6 Nov\u00e6 Hollandi\u00e6 et Insul\u00e6 Van-Diemen : exhibens characteres plantarum quas annis 1802-1805: 483.|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n*[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=2&taxon_id=105355 Flora of China: ''Calystegia'']\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commonscat-inline |Calystegia |''Calystegia''}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q149312}}\n\n[[Category:Calystegia| ]]\n[[Category:Convolvulaceae genera]]\n", "text_old": "{{automatic taxobox\n|image = Calystegia sepium ssp sepium bluete.jpeg\n|image_caption = ''[[Calystegia sepium]]''\n|image2 = Calystegia soldanella 060524wb.jpg\n|image2_caption = ''[[Calystegia soldanella]]''\n|taxon = Calystegia\n|authority = [[Robert Brown (botanist, born 1773)|R.Br.]]<ref name=IPNI/><ref name=Brown/>\n|subdivision_ranks = Species\n|subdivision = See text\n}}\n\n'''''Calystegia''''' ('''bindweed''', '''false bindweed''', or '''morning glory''') is a genus of about 25 species of [[angiosperms|flowering plant]]s in the bindweed family [[Convolvulaceae]]. The genus has a [[cosmopolitan distribution]] in temperate and subtropical regions, but with half of the species [[endemic (ecology)|endemic]] to [[California]].  They are [[annual plant|annual]] or [[herbaceous]] [[perennial plant|perennial]] twining [[vine]]s growing 1\u20135&nbsp;m tall, with spirally arranged leaves. The [[flower]]s are trumpet-shaped, 3\u201310&nbsp;cm diameter, white or pink, with a sometimes inflated basal epicalyx.\n\nThe genus bears much similarity to a related genus ''[[Convolvulus]]'', and is sometimes combined with it; it is distinguished primarily by the [[pollen]] being smooth, and in the [[ovary (plants)|ovary]] being [[Locule|unilocular]].\n\nSome of the species, notably ''[[Calystegia sepium]]'' and ''[[Calystegia silvatica|C. silvatica]]'', are problematic [[weed]]s, which can swamp other more valuable plants by climbing over them, but some are also deliberately grown for their attractive [[flower]]s.\n\n''Calystegia'' species are used as food plants by the [[larva]]e of some [[Lepidoptera]] species including ''[[Bedellia somnulentella]]'' (recorded on ''C. sepium'') and [[small angle shades]].\n\nThe name is derived from two Greek words ''kalux'', \"cup\", and ''stege'', \"a covering\", meaning \"a covering cup\". <ref> [https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/Calystegia].: Merriam-Webster dictionary:Calystegia] </ref>\n\n==Species==\nThe following species are recognised in the genus ''Calystegia'':<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://powo.science.kew.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:331450-2|title=Calystegia R.Br. {{!}} Plants of the World Online {{!}} Kew Science|website=Plants of the World Online|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n*''[[Calystegia affinis]]''\n*''[[Calystegia atriplicifolia]]'' \u2013 nightblooming false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia binghamiae]]'' \n*''[[Calystegia brummittii]]''\n*''[[Calystegia catesbiana]]'' \u2013 Catesby's false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia collina]]'' \u2013 Coast Range false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia felix]]''\n*''[[Calystegia hederacea]]'' \u2013 Japanese false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 howittiorum]]''\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 krauseana]]''\n*''[[Calystegia longipes]]'' \u2013 Paiute false bindweed, plateau morning glory \n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 lucana]]''\n*''[[Calystegia macaunii]]'' \u2013  Macoun's false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia macrostegia]]'' \u2013 island false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia malacophylla]]'' \u2013  sierra false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia marginata]]'' \u2013 small-flowered white bindweed New Zealand<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nzpcn.org.nz/flora_details.aspx?ID=229|title=Calystegia marginata {{!}} New Zealand Plant Conservation Network|website=www.nzpcn.org.nz|access-date=2018-12-10}}</ref>\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 melnikovae]]''\n*''[[Calystegia occidentalis]]'' \u2013 chaparral false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia peirsonii]]'' \u2013 Peirson's false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia pellita]]'' \u2013 hairy false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia pubescens]]\n*''[[Calystegia pulchra|Calystegia \u00d7 pulchra]]'' \u2013 hairy bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia purpurata]]'' \u2013 Pacific false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia \u00d7 scania]]''\n*''[[Calystegia sepium]]'' \u2013 large bindweed, hedge bindweed, bearbind, hedgebell ([[type species]]) \n*''[[Calystegia silvatica]]'' \u2013 great bindweed, shortstalk bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia soldanella]]'' \u2013 sea bindweed, seashore false bindweed, beach morning glory\n*''[[Calystegia spithamaea]]'' \u2013 low false bindweed, upright bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia stebbinsii]]'' \u2013 Stebbins' false bindweed, Stebbins' morning glory\n*''[[Calystegia subacaulis]]'' \u2013 hillside false bindweed\n*''[[Calystegia tuguriorium|Calystegia tuguriorum]]'' \u2013 New Zealand bindweed, p\u014duwhiwhi, p\u014dwhiwhi, rarotawake<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nzpcn.org.nz/flora_details.aspx?ID=1582|title=Calystegia tuguriorum {{!}} New Zealand Plant Conservation Network|website=www.nzpcn.org.nz|access-date=2018-12-10}}</ref>[[File:P\u014duwhiwhi_(Calystegia_tuguriorum).jpg|thumb|New Zealand bindweed]]\n*''[[Calystegia vanzuukiae]]''\n\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"200px\">\nFile:DSCM1934_Helix_Zaunwinde.jpg\nFile:Flore des serres et des jardins de l'Europe (8595873042).jpg|''[[Calystegia sepium]]'' ([[Louis van Houtte|van Houtte, L.]], 1853)\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=IPNI>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idPlantNameSearch.do?id=331450-2 |title=Convolvulaceae ''Calystegia'' R.Br. The International Plant Name Index (IPNI)|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=Brown> Brown, R. (1810) {{cite web|url=https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/36315760|title=Prodromus flor\u00e6 Nov\u00e6 Hollandi\u00e6 et Insul\u00e6 Van-Diemen : exhibens characteres plantarum quas annis 1802-1805: 483.|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n*[http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=2&taxon_id=105355 Flora of China: ''Calystegia'']\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commonscat-inline |Calystegia |''Calystegia''}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q149312}}\n\n[[Category:Calystegia| ]]\n[[Category:Convolvulaceae genera]]\n", "name_user": "Loopy30", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSpecies:trim link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calystegia"}
{"title_page": "Aitana (singer)", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|Oca\u00f1a|Morales}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Norma Arnau musica\n| background       = solo_singer\n| landscape        =\n| image            = Aitana.png\n| caption          = Aitana during a concert in Zaragoza, in 2019.\n| birth_name       = Aitana Oca\u00f1a Morales\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1999|06|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place      = [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Spain\n| partner_name     = Miguel Bernardeau\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Singer\n*songwriter\n*model}}\n| years_active     = 2017\u2013present\n| label            = [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Spain]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[electropop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Luis Cepeda|Cepeda]]\n* [[Ana Guerra]]\n* [[Miriam Rodr\u00edguez]]\n* [[Amaia (singer)|Amaia]]\n* [[Lele Pons]]\n* [[Sebasti\u00e1n Yatra]]\n* [[Lola \u00cdndigo]]\n* [[Morat (band)|Morat]]\n}}\n}}\n'''Aitana Oca\u00f1a Morales''' (born 27 June 1999), known [[mononymously]] as '''Aitana''', is a Spanish singer, songwriter and model. She first gained national recognition in 2017, placing as the runner-up in [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|series nine]] of the Spanish reality television talent competition ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]'', behind [[Amaia Romero]]. While competing in ''Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo'', Aitana released the single \"[[Lo malo]]\" with fellow competitor [[Ana Guerra]]. The song went on to become a number-one hit in Spain and was certified five times platinum, additionally being used in [[International Women's Day]] demonstrations in Spain.\n\nFollowing the competition, Aitana signed with [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Spain]] and released her debut solo single \"[[Tel\u00e9fono]]\", which became her second number-one single. Its music video became the most-watched [[Vevo]] music video within twenty-four hours  of all-time in Spain. Her debut extended play ''[[Tr\u00e1iler]]'' was released in November 2018, becoming her first chart-topping album and the second most-streamed album within twenty-four hours of all-time in Spain. The extended play's second single \"[[Vas a quedarte]]\" became her third chart-topping hit and the most-streamed song in its first twenty-four hours on [[Spotify]] Spain, surpassing the previous record which was also held by her previous release \"Tel\u00e9fono\". Her debut studio album ''[[Spoiler (album)|Spoiler]]'' (2019), was later released in June 2019 and became her second chart-topping album. Then in December 2019 she released the lead single, called \"+\", from her second studio album. It peaked at number 2 and went on to spend 9 weeks in the top 10 of the spanish official charts.\n\n== Early life ==\nAitana Oca\u00f1a Morales was born in [[Barcelona]] on 27 June 1999 to Cosme Oca\u00f1a and Bel\u00e9n Morales.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Aitana, de \"OT\": As\u00ed la ven sus padres |url=https://www.pronto.es/actualidad/aitana-ot-asi-la-ven-sus-padres-302769102.html |date=January 21, 2018 |access-date=April 18, 2018 |magazine=[[Pronto (magazine)|Pronto]] |language=es}}</ref> She grew up in the municipality of [[Sant Climent de Llobregat]], but her parents often visited [[France]] and the [[Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.20minutos.es/fotos/gente-television/los-18-concursantes-de-operacion-triunfo-2017-13510/17/ |title=Los 18 concursantes de 'Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017: Aitana |date=October 20, 2017 |access-date=March 21, 2018 |newspaper=[[20 Minutos]] |language=es}}</ref> In 2014, Aitana began to share [[cover version]]s of popular songs on [[YouTube]].<ref name=\"Prats\">{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.es/2018/01/26/ficha-de-aitana-ot-la-mas-pequena-de-la-academia-y-con-una-fuerte-pasion-por-la-musica_a_23344550/|title=Ficha de Aitana 'OT': la m\u00e1s peque\u00f1a de la Academia y con una fuerte pasi\u00f3n por la m\u00fasica|last=Prats|first=Marina|date=January 26, 2018|newspaper=[[Huffington Post]]|access-date=February 4, 2018|language=es}}</ref> In the same year, she composed her first original songs.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.culturaenserie.com/aitana-ocana-ot-2017-del-anonimato-al-triunfo-esfuerzo-humildad-voz-angelical.html |title=Aitana Oca\u00f1a (\u2018OT 2017\u2019): Del anonimato al triunfo por su esfuerzo, su humildad y su voz angelical |date=February 3, 2018 |access-date=April 18, 2018 |work=Cultura en Serie |language=es |last=Fern\u00e1ndez |first=Patricia}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she completed ''[[Education in Spain#High school (ESO y Bachillerato)|bachillerato]]'' and was admitted to study design the following year. After taking ''[[selectividad]]'', she visited [[Ciudad Universitaria (Madrid)|Ciudad Universitaria]] in [[Madrid]], where the auditions for ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]'' were being held. After auditioning, she eventually was chosen for [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|series nine]] of the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.formulatv.com/noticias/69885/operacion-triunfo-2017-madrid-casting-ciudad-universitaria-candidatos/ |title='OT 2017': Se cierra su selecci\u00f3n con un casting multitudinario en Madrid con el regreso de triunfitos |author=Redacci\u00f3n |date=July 18, 2017 |access-date=April 18, 2018 |work=Formula TV |language=es}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2017\u20132018: ''Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo'' and first releases===\n[[File:Aitana Oca\u00f1a en M\u00e1laga.jpg|thumb|Aitana in [[M\u00e1laga]] in 2018]]\nIn October 2017, Aitana entered musical reality show contest ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtve.es/television/20171020/aitana-concursante-ot/1627888.shtml|title=Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017 Aitana es concursante de OT|date=October 20, 2017|work=[[Radio Televisi\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]]|access-date=February 4, 2018|language=es}}</ref> After over three months it ended with her as the show's runner-up.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/television/20180205/44546873276/ot-2017-final-operacion-triunfo-aitana-ocana-aitana.html|title=OT: El \u2018\u00e1ngel\u2019 de Aitana, medalla de plata en la final de Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo|date=February 6, 2018|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|access-date=February 6, 2018|language=es}}</ref> During her participation in the contest, she competed to represent [[Spain in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|Spain]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]] with two songs: \"Arde\", which she performed solo, and \"Lo malo\", composed by Brisa Fenoy and performed as a duet with Ana Guerra.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/tiramillas/musica/2018/01/28/5a6b638322601d444e8b4660.html|title=Aitana de OT hace magia con 'Arde' y el jurado se rinde|date=January 30, 2018|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|access-date=February 4, 2018|language=es}}</ref> The former song ended in second place and the latter finished third in the selection.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/157631/spain-alfred-amaia-will-fly-lisbon/|title=Eurovision Spain: Alfred & Amaia will fly to Lisbon! - ESCToday.com|last=News|first=Eurovision|last2=News|first2=Participants|date=2018-01-30|website=Eurovision News, Polls and Information by ESCToday|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-22|last3=Participants|first3=Eurovision|last4=Fans}}</ref> Even though \"Lo malo\" hadn't been selected by the public to represent the country, it became an instant hit in Spain, topping the charts for [[List of number-one singles of 2018 (Spain)|five non-consecutive weeks]] and being certified 5x platinum.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elmundo.es/happy-fm/2018/02/02/5a745b6a22601d103a8b4783.html|title='Lo Malo' ya es un \u00e9xito mundial|last=War|first=Yure|date=February 2, 2018|newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|access-date=March 30, 2018|language=es}}</ref> A remix of the song featuring [[Greeicy Rend\u00f3n|Greeicy]] and [[Martina Stoessel|Tini]] was released in August 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2018/08/23/gente/1535038181_042848.html|title=\u2018Lo malo\u2019 ya tiene su remix latino|last=Pa\u00eds|first=El|date=2018-08-24|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=2019-12-22|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref> The song was performed at the [[Premios lo Nuestro|2019 Premios Lo Nuestro]] in [[Miami]].<ref>{{cite journal|last=Gonz\u00e1lez|first=Mois\u00e9s|date=February 12, 2019|title=Gabriel Soto entre los presentadores del pre-show de Premio Lo Nuestro: te contamos todas las novedades|url=https://peopleenespanol.com/television/presentadores-musicales-noche-de-estrellas-premio-lo-nuestro/|language=es|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation|Meredith Latino Network]]|access-date=February 12, 2019|magazine=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]}}</ref>\n\nAitana embarked on a co-headlining tour with her Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo mates from March to December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/programas-tv/2018-02-07/operacion-triunfo-ot2017-gira-conciertos-fechas-lugares_1527548/|title=Todas las fechas de la gira de 'Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017'|date=2018-02-07|website=El Confidencial|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> The tour consisted of 23 dates and was attended by almost 300,000 people. In July, the singer released her first solo single \"Tel\u00e9fono\" which received mixed reviews. The song became her [[List of number-one singles of 2018 (Spain)|first number-one solo song in Spain]]. It topped the charts for six consecutive weeks and was certified 4x platinum.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtve.es/television/20180803/telefono-aitana-bate-todos-records-espana/1773920.shtml|title='Tel\u00e9fono' de Aitana bate todos los r\u00e9cords en Espa\u00f1a|date=3 August 2018|work=[[RTVE]]|access-date=5 August 2018|language=es}}</ref> Its music video became the most watched video on its first twenty-four hours on [[YouTube]]'s [[Vevo]] channel in Spain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2018/07/27/actualidad/1532686480_022869.html|title=El videoclip \u2018Telefono\u2019 de Aitana supera el mill\u00f3n de visitas en unas horas|date=27 July 2018|newspaper=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|access-date=28 July 2018|publisher=Prisa|language=es}}</ref> \"Tel\u00e9fono\" was included in her debut extended play, ''[[Tr\u00e1iler]]'', which she released on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://famososlove.es/aitana-rompe-todos-los-records-con-el-lanzamiento-de-trailer|title=Aitana rompe todos los r\u00e9cords con el lanzamiento de \u2018Tr\u00e1iler\u2019|last1=L\u00f3pez|first1=D.|website=Famosos love|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> The EP features six original songs, of which one is a collaboration with the Venezuelan-American singer [[Lele Pons]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://los40.com/los40/2018/10/27/album/1540649181_018246.html|title=Tel\u00e9fono R\u00e9mix: Lele Pons, la perfecta aliada de Aitana para que 'Tel\u00e9fono' sea un hit internacional|last=Palao Murcia|first=Alberto|date=27 October 2018|work=[[Los 40]]|access-date=27 October 2018|publisher=[[Prisa]]}}</ref> A week after, \"[[Vas a quedarte|Vas a Quedarte]]\" was released as the EP's second single.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://los40.com/los40/2018/12/12/videoclips/1544622376_751110.html|title='Vas a quedarte' de Aitana\u2026 \u00a1Estreno en primicia!|last=Zavala|first=Cristina|date=13 December 2018|work=[[Los 40]]|access-date=15 December 2018|publisher=[[Prisa]]|language=es}}</ref> Written alongside Colombian band Morat, it became her third number-one hit in Spain and was nominated for \"[[Premios 40 Principales for Best Spanish Song|Song of the Year]]\" at the [[LOS40 Music Awards 2019|2019 LOS40 Music Awards]]. She also released an illustrated book which she named ''La Tinta de Mis Ojos,'' became an embassador for [[Stradivarius (clothing brand)|Stradivarius]], took part of a [[Coca-Cola]] Christmas campaign and presented Bad Bunny alongside Pons at the [[19th Annual Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mujerhoy.com/vivir/protagonistas/201806/09/aitana-ocana-publicara-libro-operacion-triunfo-20180609113704.html|title=Aitana Oca\u00f1a publicar\u00e1 su libro m\u00e1s personal|last=Gonz\u00e1lez|first=Melissa|date=9 June 2018|work=[[Mujer Hoy]]|publisher=[[Vocento]]|language=es|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lasprovincias.es/culturas/tv/anuncio-coca-cola-2018-navidad-operacion-triiunfo-20181220155456-nt.html|title=La canci\u00f3n del anuncio de Coca Cola 2018 re\u00fane a los 'triunfitos': Aitana, Ana Guerra, Lola \u00cdndigo, Raoul y Agoney, juntos por Navidad|date=21 December 2018|newspaper=[[Las Provincias]]|access-date=30 December 2018|publisher=[[Vocento]]|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=de Dios Corrales|first=Juan|date=13 November 2018|title=\u00a1Sorpresa! Aitana presentar\u00e1 en los Grammy Latinos (si es que los encuentra)|url=https://www.cuore.es/famosos/aitana-grammy-latinos-presentadora-premios|publisher=Zoom Ediciones, [[Sociedad Limitada|S.L.]]|access-date=13 November 2018|magazine=[[Cuore (magazine)|Cuore]]}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019\u2013present: Breakthrough with ''Spoiler'' ===\nAitana began teasing her debut studio album in March 2019 which was intended to be a new EP that would be the second of a trilogy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2018/10/aitana-anuncia-en-el-hormiguero-de-antena-3-que-a-finales-de-noviembre-lanzara-un-ep-de-6-canciones/|title=Aitana anuncia en El Hormiguero de Antena 3, que a finales de noviembre, lanzar\u00e1 un EP de 6 canciones|date=October 25, 2018|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref> That same month, the singer announced that she would be embarking on an intimate promotional concert tour the month after produced by [[Los 40|Los40]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2019/03/aitana-ofrecera-cuatro-conciertos-acusticos-en-los40-stage-en-abril/|title=Aitana ofrecer\u00e1 cuatro conciertos ac\u00fasticos en \u2018Los40 Stage\u2019, en abril|date=2019-03-27|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref> At the tour's first stop, in Barcelona, the singer revealed that she had changed her mind a little bit. Now, she wasn't scheduled to release another 6-track EP but a full album. She announced the album's name, ''Spoiler'' and hinted the release date of the album; she said that it would be released by the beginning of summer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://okdiario.com/happyfm/aitana-desvela-nombre-proximo-album-3967624|title=Aitana Oca\u00f1a de 'OT' desvela que el nombre de su pr\u00f3ximo \u00e1lbum es 'Spoiler'|date=April 10, 2019|website=OKDIARIO|language=es|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref> In April 2019 she collaborated with [[Morat (band)|Morat]] in \"[[Presiento]]\". In May she collaborated with former One Direction member [[Zayn Malik|Zayn]] in the revamped version of \"[[A Whole New World]]\" for the [[live action]] film of Disney's ''[[Aladdin (2019 film)|Aladdin]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cadena100.es/trending-topic/noticias/filtra-audio-aitana-cantando-con-zayn-mundo-ideal-20190510_411424|title=Se filtra el audio de Aitana cantando con Zayn \"Un mundo ideal\"|last=Villaca\u00f1as|first=Javier|date=10 May 2019|work=Cadena 100|access-date=10 June 2019|language=es}}</ref> On May 17, 2019, she released \"[[Nada sale mal|Nada Sale Mal]]\", the lead single of her upcoming debut studio album.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/3644683/0/aitana-nuevo-single-nada-sale-mal/|title=Aitana estrena 'Nada sale mal', el nuevo single del disco que est\u00e1 en camino|author=EFE|date=18 May 2019|newspaper=[[20 Minutos]]|access-date=19 May 2019|language=es|author-link=EFE}}</ref> It peaked at number 4 on the [[PROMUSICAE|Spanish charts]] and has been certified Gold. The album was released digitally and physicaly on June 7, 2019. It debuted at the top of the charts and was certified Gold in its first week. Later that month, the collaboration with [[Lola Indigo]] \"Me Quedo\" was released as the album's second single.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20190607/462715346723/spoiler-aitana-lola-indigo-me-quedo-video-seo-ext.html|title=As\u00ed suena \u2018Me quedo\u2019, lo nuevo de Aitana y Lola \u00cdndigo|date=7 June 2019|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|access-date=7 June 2019|language=es}}</ref> Thanks to this work, Aitana was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] at the [[20th Annual Latin Grammy Awards]], where she performed \"[[Mi Persona Favorita]]\" alongside [[Greeicy Rend\u00f3n|Greeicy]], Nella and [[Alejandro Sanz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/4055828/0/alejandro-sanz-rosalia-aitana-ocana-entre-los-artistas-espanoles-que-optan-a-ganar-un-latin-grammy-este-jueves/|title=Alejandro Sanz, Rosal\u00eda y Aitana, entre los espa\u00f1oles que optan esta noche a ganar un Grammy Latino|last=20minutos|date=2019-11-14|website=20minutos.es - \u00daltimas Noticias|language=es|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20191115/471616479715/alejandro-sanz-aitana-nella-greeicy-grammy-latinos-2019-mi-persona-favorita.html|title=Grammy Latinos 2019: Alejandro Sanz, Aitana, Nella y Greeicy se unen para cantar 'Mi persona favorita'|date=2019-11-15|website=La Vanguardia|language=es|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n\nThe singer embarked on her first concert tour, the [[Spoiler (album)|Play Tour]], in support of the album, on June 22, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elrescatemusical.com/entradas-play-tour-aitana/|title=\"Play Tour\": Ya a la venta las entradas de la gira de Aitana|last=Montalvo|first=Beatriz Alonso|date=2019-04-11|website=El Rescate Musical|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> With it, Aitana has been given the opportunity to sell-out large arenas like Madrid's [[Palacio Vistalegre]], Seville's Auditorio Roc\u00edo Jurado or Barcelona's [[Palau Sant Jordi]], with the last one being the country's largest indoor arena.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telecinco.es/masdetelecinco/mas-telecinco-aitana-play-tour-madrid-barcelona-entradas-taquilla_18_2806395026.html|title=Ya disponibles las entradas para el Play Tour de Aitana en Madrid y Barcelona|date=2019-08-21|website=telecinco|language=es-ES|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref> The singer performed 27 shows around Spain from June to December 2019. It has been confirmed that the tour will continue throughout 2020 in Spain and Latin America.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Aitana_DailyES/status/1207394487208689665|title={{!}} @Aitanax: \"Me voy en enero a vivir a Los \u00c1ngeles para componer, bailar, dar clases de baile y de ingl\u00e9s\". A su vuelta seguir\u00e1 componiendo, con su gira y preparando un nuevo \u00e1lbum. \u00a1Vamos a tener Aitana para rato y nueva m\u00fasica durante el 2020! pic.twitter.com/Ja5a4HkhBN|last=DailyES \u00a0\u2795|first=Aitana \u2728|date=2019-12-18|website=@Aitana_DailyES|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Se filtra el proyecto de Aitana para el 2020 y\u2026 \u00a1Vas a flipar!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ohN4v87Q-IQ|language=en|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> Thus, in February 2020 she announced the \"+ Play Tour\", its extension. It is set to begin on May 23 in Valencia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cadena100.es/musica/noticias/aitana-anuncia-las-primeras-fechas-nueva-gira-20200214_621475|title=Aitana anuncia fechas de su nueva gira|date=2020-02-14|website=CADENA 100|language=es|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n\nShortly after releasing ''Spoiler'', Aitana announced that the album would be [[reissue]]d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diezminutos.es/famosos-corazon/famosos-espanoles/a27810376/aitana-gira-spoiler/|title=La cantante Aitana habla de c\u00f3mo consigue tener los pies en la tierra|last=Diezminutos.es|first=Por|date=2019-06-07|website=Diez Minutos|language=es-ES|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> Thus, on December 3, 2019, it was released by accident on [[Spotify]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NewsAitana/status/1202149096884199427|title=\u00a1Buenos d\u00edas! Para los que nos preguntan... Ya no se pueden escuchar los ac\u00fasticos de \"SPOILER RE-PLAY\" de @Aitanax, los han bloqueado en \u2018streaming\u2019, as\u00ed que habr\u00e1 que esperar al lanzamiento oficial para volver a disfrutar de ellos. \u00a1Ya queda menos!|last=Aitana \u271a|first=News|date=2019-12-04|website=@NewsAitana|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> After removing it shortly after, the singer announced \"''Spoiler: Re-Play''\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elrescatemusical.com/aitana-anuncia-spoiler-re-play-dvd/|title=Aitana publicar\u00e1 \u2018Spoiler Re-play\u2019, edici\u00f3n especial de su primer \u00e1lbum con DVD|last=Musical|first=El Rescate|date=2019-12-16|website=El Rescate Musical|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> Released on December 20, 2019, the reissue includes the album, five acoustic versions of her own songs and a tour documentary that features images of her concerts in [[Madrid]], Barcelona and [[Granada]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/UniversalSpain/status/1208039556131573760|title=.@Aitanax presenta hoy la edici\u00f3n especial \"SPOILER RE-PLAY\" que incluye el audio de \"SPOILER\" adem\u00e1s de 1 hora aproximadamente de contenido exclusivo en DVD: Documental de la gira y 5 temas en ac\u00fastico https://umusices.lnk.to/AsrpTP\u00a0pic.twitter.com/guKMmZ3L4x|last=UniversalMusicSpain|date=2019-12-20|website=@UniversalSpain|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> It hasn't been released in digital platforms but only in physical stores. Aitana ended 2019 being the third most streamed female artist on Sportify in Spain only being surpassed by flamenco fusion singer [[Rosal\u00eda (singer)|Rosal\u00eda]] and Colombian singer [[Karol G]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eltelevisero.com/2019/12/rosalia-aitana-y-lola-indigo-entre-las-artistas-mas-reproducidas-en-spotify/|title=Rosal\u00eda, Aitana y Lola \u00cdndigo: entre las artistas m\u00e1s reproducidas en Spotify|date=2019-12-04|website=El Televisero|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\nOn December 18, 2019, Aitana released the lead single of her upcoming second studio album. She anticipated during fall that it would feature an internationally-known artist. Thus on the mentioned day she released \"[[+ (song)|+]]\" featuring Colombian duo [[Cali y El Dandee|Cali Y el Dandee]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rtve.es/playz/20191204/aitana-sorprende-anunciando-colaboracion-cali-dandee/1993193.shtml|title=Aitana sorprende a sus seguidores anunciando su colaboraci\u00f3n con Cali y Dandee|last=PLAYZ|date=2019-12-04|website=RTVE.es|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> The song debuted at number 21 on the PROMUSICAE chart with only two days of tracking making it the only song in Spanish music history to reach this position with within this 2 days, later peaking at number 2 and spending 9 weeks in the top 10.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2019/12/de-aitana-y-cali-y-el-dandee-mejor-debut-historico-en-la-lista-espanola-con-48-horas-o-menos-de-publicacion/|title=\"+\" de Aitana y Cali Y El Dandee, mejor debut hist\u00f3rico en la lista espa\u00f1ola, con 48 horas o menos de publicaci\u00f3n|date=2019-12-26|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref> On December 28, 2019, it was announced that Aitana will have a cameo role in the third season of the original Spanish [[Netflix]] series, [[Elite (TV series)|Elite]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://los40.com/los40/2019/12/27/cinetv/1577468833_803912.html|title=Aitana tiene un cameo en la tercera temporada de \u2018\u00c9lite\u2019|publisher=Los 40|date=December 28, 2019|accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref> The singer will be back on TV as a judge on the upcoming season of ''[[La Voz Kids (Spanish TV series)|La Voz Kids]]'', which is set to premiere in late 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://as.com/tikitakas/2020/02/10/portada/1581347643_260708.html|title=Aitana ficha por 'La Voz Kids' y Bisbal vuelve a mostrarle su admiraci\u00f3n|date=2020-02-10|website=AS.com|language=es|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 January 2020 she won premio Ode\u00f3n for Best New Artist.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abc.es/estilo/abci-aitana-gana-premio-odeon-artista-revelacion-202001211157_video.html |title=Aitana gana el premio Ode\u00f3n a la Artista Revelaci\u00f3n |date=21 January 2020 |access-date=23 January 2020 |newspaper=[[ABC (Spain)|ABC]] |publisher=[[Vocento]] |language=es |author=Europa Press |author-link=Europa Press (news agency)}}</ref> In April 2020 she collaborated with Spanish singer and fellow friend David Bisbal on the remix of his song \"[[Si t\u00fa la quieres|Si T\u00fa la Quieres]]\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://los40.com/los40/2020/03/30/musica/1585600448_205423.html |title='Si t\u00fa la quieres', el tema de David Bisbal y Aitana |first=Cristina |last=Zavala |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |work=[[Los 40]]}}</ref> \n\n==Discography==\n{{main|Aitana discography}}\n*''[[Spoiler (album)|Spoiler]]'' (2019)\n\n== Tour ==\n'''Headlining'''\n\n*[[Play Tour]] (2019-2020)\n\n'''Co-headlining'''\n\n* OT 2017 en concierto (2018) <small>(with [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017]])</small>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Ceremony\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2018\n|[[2018 Radio Disney Music Awards|Radio Disney Music Awards]]\n|Best Spanish Act\n|Aitana y Ana Guerra\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/newsaitana/status/1013173985717211137|title=Aitana y Ana Guerra acaban de ganar el premio 'Radio Disney Music Awards' como 'Estrella espa\u00f1ola m\u00e1s brillante'  \u00a1Enhorabuena chicas! #RDMApic.twitter.com/daYTc8lTSt|last=Aitana \u271a|first=News|date=2018-06-30|website=@newsaitana|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n|-\n|Cosmo Awards\n|Girl Gang Award\n|Herself\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lecturas.com/esta-pasando/video-aitana-y-ana-guerra-bailando-lo-malo-premios-cosmopolitan_57640|title=El v\u00eddeo de Aitana y Ana Guerra bailando 'Lo Malo' en los premios Cosmopolitan|date=2018-10-19|website=Lecturas|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[LOS40 Music Awards 2018|LOS40 Music Awards]]\n|Best New Artist\n|Aitana y Ana Guerra\n|{{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2018/ganadores/|title=Ganadores|publisher=Los40|language=Spanish|accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Song of the Year\n|\"[[Lo malo|Lo Malo]]\"\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2019\n| [[2019 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]] \n| Favorite Spanish Artist\n| rowspan=\"4\" |Herself\n| {{won}}\n| align=center| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://nickalive.blogspot.com/2019/02/nickelodeon-kids-choice-awards-2019.html|title=Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards 2019 International Nominees & Winners|publisher=NickALive|date=29 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[BreakTudo Awards 2019|BreakTudo Awards]]\n| International New Artist \n| {{nom}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/08/breaktudo-awards-2019-blackpink-bts-and-red-velvet-received-multiple-nominations|title=BreakTudo Awards 2019: BlackPink, BTS and Red Velvet received multiple nominations|date=22 August 2019|publisher=AllKpop|last=Nakama|first=Kyle}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[20th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy Awards]]\n|[[Latin Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]]\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20191115/471615325362/ganadores-grammy-latinos-2019-lista-completa.html|title=Todos los ganadores de los Grammy Latinos 2019|last=None|first=Por Redacci\u00f3n|date=2019-11-15|website=La Vanguardia|language=es-ES|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[LOS40 Music Awards 2019|LOS40 Music Awards]]\n| Artist of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| align=center rowspan=\"4\" |<ref>{{Cite web|title= Nominados de LOS40 Music Awards 2019|url =https://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2019/nominados/|work= Los 40 |access-date= 2016-08-19|language= es}}</ref>\n|-\n| Song of the Year\n|\"[[Vas a quedarte|Vas a Quedarte]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Video of the Year\n|\"Me Quedo\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Del 40 al 1 Artist Award\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Herself\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2020\n| rowspan=\"5\" |Premios Ode\u00f3n\n|Best Female Artist\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://us.hola.com/actualidad/20191223156888/premios-odeon-musica-espanola/|title=Rosal\u00eda, Leiva o Amaia nominados a los nuevos Premios Ode\u00f3n|date=2019-12-23|website=HOLA USA|language=es-US|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best New Artist\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|Best Album\n|''[[Spoiler (album)|Spoiler]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Song\n|\"[[Presiento]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Music Video\n|\"[[Tel\u00e9fono]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Premios Dial\n|Best Artist\n|Herself\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cadenadial.com/2020/premios-dial-ganadores-actuaciones-y-premios-especiales-182692.html|title=Premios Dial \u00a1ganadores, actuaciones y premios especiales!|date=2020-02-26|website=Cadena Dial|language=es-ES|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{Twitter|Aitanax}}\n* {{Instagram|Aitanax}}\n* {{IMDb name|9380750}}\n* {{YouTube|channel=UCI505QHIvSgj8lbHY7ygE1A}}\n\n{{Aitana (singer)|state=collapsed}}\n{{Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aitana}}\n[[Category:Singers from Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Spanish female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Spanish female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo contestants]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Group artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|Oca\u00f1a|Morales}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Aitana\n| background       = solo_singer\n| landscape        =\n| image            = Aitana.png\n| caption          = Aitana during a concert in Zaragoza, in 2019.\n| birth_name       = Aitana Oca\u00f1a Morales\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1999|06|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place      = [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Spain\n| partner_name     = Miguel Bernardeau\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Singer\n*songwriter\n*model}}\n| years_active     = 2017\u2013present\n| label            = [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Spain]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[electropop]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Luis Cepeda|Cepeda]]\n* [[Ana Guerra]]\n* [[Miriam Rodr\u00edguez]]\n* [[Amaia (singer)|Amaia]]\n* [[Lele Pons]]\n* [[Sebasti\u00e1n Yatra]]\n* [[Lola \u00cdndigo]]\n* [[Morat (band)|Morat]]\n}}\n}}\n'''Aitana Oca\u00f1a Morales''' (born 27 June 1999), known [[mononymously]] as '''Aitana''', is a Spanish singer, songwriter and model. She first gained national recognition in 2017, placing as the runner-up in [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|series nine]] of the Spanish reality television talent competition ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]'', behind [[Amaia Romero]]. While competing in ''Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo'', Aitana released the single \"[[Lo malo]]\" with fellow competitor [[Ana Guerra]]. The song went on to become a number-one hit in Spain and was certified five times platinum, additionally being used in [[International Women's Day]] demonstrations in Spain.\n\nFollowing the competition, Aitana signed with [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Spain]] and released her debut solo single \"[[Tel\u00e9fono]]\", which became her second number-one single. Its music video became the most-watched [[Vevo]] music video within twenty-four hours  of all-time in Spain. Her debut extended play ''[[Tr\u00e1iler]]'' was released in November 2018, becoming her first chart-topping album and the second most-streamed album within twenty-four hours of all-time in Spain. The extended play's second single \"[[Vas a quedarte]]\" became her third chart-topping hit and the most-streamed song in its first twenty-four hours on [[Spotify]] Spain, surpassing the previous record which was also held by her previous release \"Tel\u00e9fono\". Her debut studio album ''[[Spoiler (album)|Spoiler]]'' (2019), was later released in June 2019 and became her second chart-topping album. Then in December 2019 she released the lead single, called \"+\", from her second studio album. It peaked at number 2 and went on to spend 9 weeks in the top 10 of the spanish official charts.\n\n== Early life ==\nAitana Oca\u00f1a Morales was born in [[Barcelona]] on 27 June 1999 to Cosme Oca\u00f1a and Bel\u00e9n Morales.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Aitana, de \"OT\": As\u00ed la ven sus padres |url=https://www.pronto.es/actualidad/aitana-ot-asi-la-ven-sus-padres-302769102.html |date=January 21, 2018 |access-date=April 18, 2018 |magazine=[[Pronto (magazine)|Pronto]] |language=es}}</ref> She grew up in the municipality of [[Sant Climent de Llobregat]], but her parents often visited [[France]] and the [[Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.20minutos.es/fotos/gente-television/los-18-concursantes-de-operacion-triunfo-2017-13510/17/ |title=Los 18 concursantes de 'Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017: Aitana |date=October 20, 2017 |access-date=March 21, 2018 |newspaper=[[20 Minutos]] |language=es}}</ref> In 2014, Aitana began to share [[cover version]]s of popular songs on [[YouTube]].<ref name=\"Prats\">{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.es/2018/01/26/ficha-de-aitana-ot-la-mas-pequena-de-la-academia-y-con-una-fuerte-pasion-por-la-musica_a_23344550/|title=Ficha de Aitana 'OT': la m\u00e1s peque\u00f1a de la Academia y con una fuerte pasi\u00f3n por la m\u00fasica|last=Prats|first=Marina|date=January 26, 2018|newspaper=[[Huffington Post]]|access-date=February 4, 2018|language=es}}</ref> In the same year, she composed her first original songs.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.culturaenserie.com/aitana-ocana-ot-2017-del-anonimato-al-triunfo-esfuerzo-humildad-voz-angelical.html |title=Aitana Oca\u00f1a (\u2018OT 2017\u2019): Del anonimato al triunfo por su esfuerzo, su humildad y su voz angelical |date=February 3, 2018 |access-date=April 18, 2018 |work=Cultura en Serie |language=es |last=Fern\u00e1ndez |first=Patricia}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she completed ''[[Education in Spain#High school (ESO y Bachillerato)|bachillerato]]'' and was admitted to study design the following year. After taking ''[[selectividad]]'', she visited [[Ciudad Universitaria (Madrid)|Ciudad Universitaria]] in [[Madrid]], where the auditions for ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]'' were being held. After auditioning, she eventually was chosen for [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|series nine]] of the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.formulatv.com/noticias/69885/operacion-triunfo-2017-madrid-casting-ciudad-universitaria-candidatos/ |title='OT 2017': Se cierra su selecci\u00f3n con un casting multitudinario en Madrid con el regreso de triunfitos |author=Redacci\u00f3n |date=July 18, 2017 |access-date=April 18, 2018 |work=Formula TV |language=es}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== 2017\u20132018: ''Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo'' and first releases===\n[[File:Aitana Oca\u00f1a en M\u00e1laga.jpg|thumb|Aitana in [[M\u00e1laga]] in 2018]]\nIn October 2017, Aitana entered musical reality show contest ''[[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (Spanish TV series)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtve.es/television/20171020/aitana-concursante-ot/1627888.shtml|title=Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017 Aitana es concursante de OT|date=October 20, 2017|work=[[Radio Televisi\u00f3n Espa\u00f1ola]]|access-date=February 4, 2018|language=es}}</ref> After over three months it ended with her as the show's runner-up.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/television/20180205/44546873276/ot-2017-final-operacion-triunfo-aitana-ocana-aitana.html|title=OT: El \u2018\u00e1ngel\u2019 de Aitana, medalla de plata en la final de Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo|date=February 6, 2018|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|access-date=February 6, 2018|language=es}}</ref> During her participation in the contest, she competed to represent [[Spain in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|Spain]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2018]] with two songs: \"Arde\", which she performed solo, and \"Lo malo\", composed by Brisa Fenoy and performed as a duet with Ana Guerra.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/tiramillas/musica/2018/01/28/5a6b638322601d444e8b4660.html|title=Aitana de OT hace magia con 'Arde' y el jurado se rinde|date=January 30, 2018|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|access-date=February 4, 2018|language=es}}</ref> The former song ended in second place and the latter finished third in the selection.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://esctoday.com/157631/spain-alfred-amaia-will-fly-lisbon/|title=Eurovision Spain: Alfred & Amaia will fly to Lisbon! - ESCToday.com|last=News|first=Eurovision|last2=News|first2=Participants|date=2018-01-30|website=Eurovision News, Polls and Information by ESCToday|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-22|last3=Participants|first3=Eurovision|last4=Fans}}</ref> Even though \"Lo malo\" hadn't been selected by the public to represent the country, it became an instant hit in Spain, topping the charts for [[List of number-one singles of 2018 (Spain)|five non-consecutive weeks]] and being certified 5x platinum.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elmundo.es/happy-fm/2018/02/02/5a745b6a22601d103a8b4783.html|title='Lo Malo' ya es un \u00e9xito mundial|last=War|first=Yure|date=February 2, 2018|newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|access-date=March 30, 2018|language=es}}</ref> A remix of the song featuring [[Greeicy Rend\u00f3n|Greeicy]] and [[Martina Stoessel|Tini]] was released in August 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2018/08/23/gente/1535038181_042848.html|title=\u2018Lo malo\u2019 ya tiene su remix latino|last=Pa\u00eds|first=El|date=2018-08-24|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=2019-12-22|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref> The song was performed at the [[Premios lo Nuestro|2019 Premios Lo Nuestro]] in [[Miami]].<ref>{{cite journal|last=Gonz\u00e1lez|first=Mois\u00e9s|date=February 12, 2019|title=Gabriel Soto entre los presentadores del pre-show de Premio Lo Nuestro: te contamos todas las novedades|url=https://peopleenespanol.com/television/presentadores-musicales-noche-de-estrellas-premio-lo-nuestro/|language=es|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation|Meredith Latino Network]]|access-date=February 12, 2019|magazine=[[People en Espa\u00f1ol]]}}</ref>\n\nAitana embarked on a co-headlining tour with her Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo mates from March to December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/television/programas-tv/2018-02-07/operacion-triunfo-ot2017-gira-conciertos-fechas-lugares_1527548/|title=Todas las fechas de la gira de 'Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017'|date=2018-02-07|website=El Confidencial|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> The tour consisted of 23 dates and was attended by almost 300,000 people. In July, the singer released her first solo single \"Tel\u00e9fono\" which received mixed reviews. The song became her [[List of number-one singles of 2018 (Spain)|first number-one solo song in Spain]]. It topped the charts for six consecutive weeks and was certified 4x platinum.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtve.es/television/20180803/telefono-aitana-bate-todos-records-espana/1773920.shtml|title='Tel\u00e9fono' de Aitana bate todos los r\u00e9cords en Espa\u00f1a|date=3 August 2018|work=[[RTVE]]|access-date=5 August 2018|language=es}}</ref> Its music video became the most watched video on its first twenty-four hours on [[YouTube]]'s [[Vevo]] channel in Spain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/cultura/2018/07/27/actualidad/1532686480_022869.html|title=El videoclip \u2018Telefono\u2019 de Aitana supera el mill\u00f3n de visitas en unas horas|date=27 July 2018|newspaper=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|access-date=28 July 2018|publisher=Prisa|language=es}}</ref> \"Tel\u00e9fono\" was included in her debut extended play, ''[[Tr\u00e1iler]]'', which she released on November 30, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://famososlove.es/aitana-rompe-todos-los-records-con-el-lanzamiento-de-trailer|title=Aitana rompe todos los r\u00e9cords con el lanzamiento de \u2018Tr\u00e1iler\u2019|last1=L\u00f3pez|first1=D.|website=Famosos love|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref> The EP features six original songs, of which one is a collaboration with the Venezuelan-American singer [[Lele Pons]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://los40.com/los40/2018/10/27/album/1540649181_018246.html|title=Tel\u00e9fono R\u00e9mix: Lele Pons, la perfecta aliada de Aitana para que 'Tel\u00e9fono' sea un hit internacional|last=Palao Murcia|first=Alberto|date=27 October 2018|work=[[Los 40]]|access-date=27 October 2018|publisher=[[Prisa]]}}</ref> A week after, \"[[Vas a quedarte|Vas a Quedarte]]\" was released as the EP's second single.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://los40.com/los40/2018/12/12/videoclips/1544622376_751110.html|title='Vas a quedarte' de Aitana\u2026 \u00a1Estreno en primicia!|last=Zavala|first=Cristina|date=13 December 2018|work=[[Los 40]]|access-date=15 December 2018|publisher=[[Prisa]]|language=es}}</ref> Written alongside Colombian band Morat, it became her third number-one hit in Spain and was nominated for \"[[Premios 40 Principales for Best Spanish Song|Song of the Year]]\" at the [[LOS40 Music Awards 2019|2019 LOS40 Music Awards]]. She also released an illustrated book which she named ''La Tinta de Mis Ojos,'' became an embassador for [[Stradivarius (clothing brand)|Stradivarius]], took part of a [[Coca-Cola]] Christmas campaign and presented Bad Bunny alongside Pons at the [[19th Annual Latin Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mujerhoy.com/vivir/protagonistas/201806/09/aitana-ocana-publicara-libro-operacion-triunfo-20180609113704.html|title=Aitana Oca\u00f1a publicar\u00e1 su libro m\u00e1s personal|last=Gonz\u00e1lez|first=Melissa|date=9 June 2018|work=[[Mujer Hoy]]|publisher=[[Vocento]]|language=es|access-date=17 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lasprovincias.es/culturas/tv/anuncio-coca-cola-2018-navidad-operacion-triiunfo-20181220155456-nt.html|title=La canci\u00f3n del anuncio de Coca Cola 2018 re\u00fane a los 'triunfitos': Aitana, Ana Guerra, Lola \u00cdndigo, Raoul y Agoney, juntos por Navidad|date=21 December 2018|newspaper=[[Las Provincias]]|access-date=30 December 2018|publisher=[[Vocento]]|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=de Dios Corrales|first=Juan|date=13 November 2018|title=\u00a1Sorpresa! Aitana presentar\u00e1 en los Grammy Latinos (si es que los encuentra)|url=https://www.cuore.es/famosos/aitana-grammy-latinos-presentadora-premios|publisher=Zoom Ediciones, [[Sociedad Limitada|S.L.]]|access-date=13 November 2018|magazine=[[Cuore (magazine)|Cuore]]}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019\u2013present: Breakthrough with ''Spoiler'' ===\nAitana began teasing her debut studio album in March 2019 which was intended to be a new EP that would be the second of a trilogy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2018/10/aitana-anuncia-en-el-hormiguero-de-antena-3-que-a-finales-de-noviembre-lanzara-un-ep-de-6-canciones/|title=Aitana anuncia en El Hormiguero de Antena 3, que a finales de noviembre, lanzar\u00e1 un EP de 6 canciones|date=October 25, 2018|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref> That same month, the singer announced that she would be embarking on an intimate promotional concert tour the month after produced by [[Los 40|Los40]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2019/03/aitana-ofrecera-cuatro-conciertos-acusticos-en-los40-stage-en-abril/|title=Aitana ofrecer\u00e1 cuatro conciertos ac\u00fasticos en \u2018Los40 Stage\u2019, en abril|date=2019-03-27|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=2019-07-26}}</ref> At the tour's first stop, in Barcelona, the singer revealed that she had changed her mind a little bit. Now, she wasn't scheduled to release another 6-track EP but a full album. She announced the album's name, ''Spoiler'' and hinted the release date of the album; she said that it would be released by the beginning of summer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://okdiario.com/happyfm/aitana-desvela-nombre-proximo-album-3967624|title=Aitana Oca\u00f1a de 'OT' desvela que el nombre de su pr\u00f3ximo \u00e1lbum es 'Spoiler'|date=April 10, 2019|website=OKDIARIO|language=es|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref> In April 2019 she collaborated with [[Morat (band)|Morat]] in \"[[Presiento]]\". In May she collaborated with former One Direction member [[Zayn Malik|Zayn]] in the revamped version of \"[[A Whole New World]]\" for the [[live action]] film of Disney's ''[[Aladdin (2019 film)|Aladdin]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cadena100.es/trending-topic/noticias/filtra-audio-aitana-cantando-con-zayn-mundo-ideal-20190510_411424|title=Se filtra el audio de Aitana cantando con Zayn \"Un mundo ideal\"|last=Villaca\u00f1as|first=Javier|date=10 May 2019|work=Cadena 100|access-date=10 June 2019|language=es}}</ref> On May 17, 2019, she released \"[[Nada sale mal|Nada Sale Mal]]\", the lead single of her upcoming debut studio album.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/3644683/0/aitana-nuevo-single-nada-sale-mal/|title=Aitana estrena 'Nada sale mal', el nuevo single del disco que est\u00e1 en camino|author=EFE|date=18 May 2019|newspaper=[[20 Minutos]]|access-date=19 May 2019|language=es|author-link=EFE}}</ref> It peaked at number 4 on the [[PROMUSICAE|Spanish charts]] and has been certified Gold. The album was released digitally and physicaly on June 7, 2019. It debuted at the top of the charts and was certified Gold in its first week. Later that month, the collaboration with [[Lola Indigo]] \"Me Quedo\" was released as the album's second single.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20190607/462715346723/spoiler-aitana-lola-indigo-me-quedo-video-seo-ext.html|title=As\u00ed suena \u2018Me quedo\u2019, lo nuevo de Aitana y Lola \u00cdndigo|date=7 June 2019|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|access-date=7 June 2019|language=es}}</ref> Thanks to this work, Aitana was nominated for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] at the [[20th Annual Latin Grammy Awards]], where she performed \"[[Mi Persona Favorita]]\" alongside [[Greeicy Rend\u00f3n|Greeicy]], Nella and [[Alejandro Sanz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/4055828/0/alejandro-sanz-rosalia-aitana-ocana-entre-los-artistas-espanoles-que-optan-a-ganar-un-latin-grammy-este-jueves/|title=Alejandro Sanz, Rosal\u00eda y Aitana, entre los espa\u00f1oles que optan esta noche a ganar un Grammy Latino|last=20minutos|date=2019-11-14|website=20minutos.es - \u00daltimas Noticias|language=es|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20191115/471616479715/alejandro-sanz-aitana-nella-greeicy-grammy-latinos-2019-mi-persona-favorita.html|title=Grammy Latinos 2019: Alejandro Sanz, Aitana, Nella y Greeicy se unen para cantar 'Mi persona favorita'|date=2019-11-15|website=La Vanguardia|language=es|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n\nThe singer embarked on her first concert tour, the [[Spoiler (album)|Play Tour]], in support of the album, on June 22, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elrescatemusical.com/entradas-play-tour-aitana/|title=\"Play Tour\": Ya a la venta las entradas de la gira de Aitana|last=Montalvo|first=Beatriz Alonso|date=2019-04-11|website=El Rescate Musical|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> With it, Aitana has been given the opportunity to sell-out large arenas like Madrid's [[Palacio Vistalegre]], Seville's Auditorio Roc\u00edo Jurado or Barcelona's [[Palau Sant Jordi]], with the last one being the country's largest indoor arena.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telecinco.es/masdetelecinco/mas-telecinco-aitana-play-tour-madrid-barcelona-entradas-taquilla_18_2806395026.html|title=Ya disponibles las entradas para el Play Tour de Aitana en Madrid y Barcelona|date=2019-08-21|website=telecinco|language=es-ES|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref> The singer performed 27 shows around Spain from June to December 2019. It has been confirmed that the tour will continue throughout 2020 in Spain and Latin America.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Aitana_DailyES/status/1207394487208689665|title={{!}} @Aitanax: \"Me voy en enero a vivir a Los \u00c1ngeles para componer, bailar, dar clases de baile y de ingl\u00e9s\". A su vuelta seguir\u00e1 componiendo, con su gira y preparando un nuevo \u00e1lbum. \u00a1Vamos a tener Aitana para rato y nueva m\u00fasica durante el 2020! pic.twitter.com/Ja5a4HkhBN|last=DailyES \u00a0\u2795|first=Aitana \u2728|date=2019-12-18|website=@Aitana_DailyES|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Se filtra el proyecto de Aitana para el 2020 y\u2026 \u00a1Vas a flipar!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ohN4v87Q-IQ|language=en|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> Thus, in February 2020 she announced the \"+ Play Tour\", its extension. It is set to begin on May 23 in Valencia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cadena100.es/musica/noticias/aitana-anuncia-las-primeras-fechas-nueva-gira-20200214_621475|title=Aitana anuncia fechas de su nueva gira|date=2020-02-14|website=CADENA 100|language=es|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n\nShortly after releasing ''Spoiler'', Aitana announced that the album would be [[reissue]]d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diezminutos.es/famosos-corazon/famosos-espanoles/a27810376/aitana-gira-spoiler/|title=La cantante Aitana habla de c\u00f3mo consigue tener los pies en la tierra|last=Diezminutos.es|first=Por|date=2019-06-07|website=Diez Minutos|language=es-ES|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> Thus, on December 3, 2019, it was released by accident on [[Spotify]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NewsAitana/status/1202149096884199427|title=\u00a1Buenos d\u00edas! Para los que nos preguntan... Ya no se pueden escuchar los ac\u00fasticos de \"SPOILER RE-PLAY\" de @Aitanax, los han bloqueado en \u2018streaming\u2019, as\u00ed que habr\u00e1 que esperar al lanzamiento oficial para volver a disfrutar de ellos. \u00a1Ya queda menos!|last=Aitana \u271a|first=News|date=2019-12-04|website=@NewsAitana|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> After removing it shortly after, the singer announced \"''Spoiler: Re-Play''\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elrescatemusical.com/aitana-anuncia-spoiler-re-play-dvd/|title=Aitana publicar\u00e1 \u2018Spoiler Re-play\u2019, edici\u00f3n especial de su primer \u00e1lbum con DVD|last=Musical|first=El Rescate|date=2019-12-16|website=El Rescate Musical|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> Released on December 20, 2019, the reissue includes the album, five acoustic versions of her own songs and a tour documentary that features images of her concerts in [[Madrid]], Barcelona and [[Granada]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/UniversalSpain/status/1208039556131573760|title=.@Aitanax presenta hoy la edici\u00f3n especial \"SPOILER RE-PLAY\" que incluye el audio de \"SPOILER\" adem\u00e1s de 1 hora aproximadamente de contenido exclusivo en DVD: Documental de la gira y 5 temas en ac\u00fastico https://umusices.lnk.to/AsrpTP\u00a0pic.twitter.com/guKMmZ3L4x|last=UniversalMusicSpain|date=2019-12-20|website=@UniversalSpain|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> It hasn't been released in digital platforms but only in physical stores. Aitana ended 2019 being the third most streamed female artist on Sportify in Spain only being surpassed by flamenco fusion singer [[Rosal\u00eda (singer)|Rosal\u00eda]] and Colombian singer [[Karol G]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eltelevisero.com/2019/12/rosalia-aitana-y-lola-indigo-entre-las-artistas-mas-reproducidas-en-spotify/|title=Rosal\u00eda, Aitana y Lola \u00cdndigo: entre las artistas m\u00e1s reproducidas en Spotify|date=2019-12-04|website=El Televisero|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\nOn December 18, 2019, Aitana released the lead single of her upcoming second studio album. She anticipated during fall that it would feature an internationally-known artist. Thus on the mentioned day she released \"[[+ (song)|+]]\" featuring Colombian duo [[Cali y El Dandee|Cali Y el Dandee]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rtve.es/playz/20191204/aitana-sorprende-anunciando-colaboracion-cali-dandee/1993193.shtml|title=Aitana sorprende a sus seguidores anunciando su colaboraci\u00f3n con Cali y Dandee|last=PLAYZ|date=2019-12-04|website=RTVE.es|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref> The song debuted at number 21 on the PROMUSICAE chart with only two days of tracking making it the only song in Spanish music history to reach this position with within this 2 days, later peaking at number 2 and spending 9 weeks in the top 10.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vinilonegro.com/2019/12/de-aitana-y-cali-y-el-dandee-mejor-debut-historico-en-la-lista-espanola-con-48-horas-o-menos-de-publicacion/|title=\"+\" de Aitana y Cali Y El Dandee, mejor debut hist\u00f3rico en la lista espa\u00f1ola, con 48 horas o menos de publicaci\u00f3n|date=2019-12-26|website=Vinilo Negro|language=es|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref> On December 28, 2019, it was announced that Aitana will have a cameo role in the third season of the original Spanish [[Netflix]] series, [[Elite (TV series)|Elite]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://los40.com/los40/2019/12/27/cinetv/1577468833_803912.html|title=Aitana tiene un cameo en la tercera temporada de \u2018\u00c9lite\u2019|publisher=Los 40|date=December 28, 2019|accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref> The singer will be back on TV as a judge on the upcoming season of ''[[La Voz Kids (Spanish TV series)|La Voz Kids]]'', which is set to premiere in late 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://as.com/tikitakas/2020/02/10/portada/1581347643_260708.html|title=Aitana ficha por 'La Voz Kids' y Bisbal vuelve a mostrarle su admiraci\u00f3n|date=2020-02-10|website=AS.com|language=es|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 January 2020 she won premio Ode\u00f3n for Best New Artist.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abc.es/estilo/abci-aitana-gana-premio-odeon-artista-revelacion-202001211157_video.html |title=Aitana gana el premio Ode\u00f3n a la Artista Revelaci\u00f3n |date=21 January 2020 |access-date=23 January 2020 |newspaper=[[ABC (Spain)|ABC]] |publisher=[[Vocento]] |language=es |author=Europa Press |author-link=Europa Press (news agency)}}</ref> In April 2020 she collaborated with Spanish singer and fellow friend David Bisbal on the remix of his song \"[[Si t\u00fa la quieres|Si T\u00fa la Quieres]]\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://los40.com/los40/2020/03/30/musica/1585600448_205423.html |title='Si t\u00fa la quieres', el tema de David Bisbal y Aitana |first=Cristina |last=Zavala |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |work=[[Los 40]]}}</ref> \n\n==Discography==\n{{main|Aitana discography}}\n*''[[Spoiler (album)|Spoiler]]'' (2019)\n\n== Tour ==\n'''Headlining'''\n\n*[[Play Tour]] (2019-2020)\n\n'''Co-headlining'''\n\n* OT 2017 en concierto (2018) <small>(with [[Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo (series 9)|Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo 2017]])</small>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Ceremony\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2018\n|[[2018 Radio Disney Music Awards|Radio Disney Music Awards]]\n|Best Spanish Act\n|Aitana y Ana Guerra\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/newsaitana/status/1013173985717211137|title=Aitana y Ana Guerra acaban de ganar el premio 'Radio Disney Music Awards' como 'Estrella espa\u00f1ola m\u00e1s brillante'  \u00a1Enhorabuena chicas! #RDMApic.twitter.com/daYTc8lTSt|last=Aitana \u271a|first=News|date=2018-06-30|website=@newsaitana|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n|-\n|Cosmo Awards\n|Girl Gang Award\n|Herself\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lecturas.com/esta-pasando/video-aitana-y-ana-guerra-bailando-lo-malo-premios-cosmopolitan_57640|title=El v\u00eddeo de Aitana y Ana Guerra bailando 'Lo Malo' en los premios Cosmopolitan|date=2018-10-19|website=Lecturas|language=es|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[LOS40 Music Awards 2018|LOS40 Music Awards]]\n|Best New Artist\n|Aitana y Ana Guerra\n|{{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2018/ganadores/|title=Ganadores|publisher=Los40|language=Spanish|accessdate=5 October 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Song of the Year\n|\"[[Lo malo|Lo Malo]]\"\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2019\n| [[2019 Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]] \n| Favorite Spanish Artist\n| rowspan=\"4\" |Herself\n| {{won}}\n| align=center| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://nickalive.blogspot.com/2019/02/nickelodeon-kids-choice-awards-2019.html|title=Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards 2019 International Nominees & Winners|publisher=NickALive|date=29 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[BreakTudo Awards 2019|BreakTudo Awards]]\n| International New Artist \n| {{nom}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/08/breaktudo-awards-2019-blackpink-bts-and-red-velvet-received-multiple-nominations|title=BreakTudo Awards 2019: BlackPink, BTS and Red Velvet received multiple nominations|date=22 August 2019|publisher=AllKpop|last=Nakama|first=Kyle}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[20th Annual Latin Grammy Awards|Latin Grammy Awards]]\n|[[Latin Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]]\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/musica/20191115/471615325362/ganadores-grammy-latinos-2019-lista-completa.html|title=Todos los ganadores de los Grammy Latinos 2019|last=None|first=Por Redacci\u00f3n|date=2019-11-15|website=La Vanguardia|language=es-ES|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[LOS40 Music Awards 2019|LOS40 Music Awards]]\n| Artist of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| align=center rowspan=\"4\" |<ref>{{Cite web|title= Nominados de LOS40 Music Awards 2019|url =https://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2019/nominados/|work= Los 40 |access-date= 2016-08-19|language= es}}</ref>\n|-\n| Song of the Year\n|\"[[Vas a quedarte|Vas a Quedarte]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Video of the Year\n|\"Me Quedo\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Del 40 al 1 Artist Award\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Herself\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | 2020\n| rowspan=\"5\" |Premios Ode\u00f3n\n|Best Female Artist\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://us.hola.com/actualidad/20191223156888/premios-odeon-musica-espanola/|title=Rosal\u00eda, Leiva o Amaia nominados a los nuevos Premios Ode\u00f3n|date=2019-12-23|website=HOLA USA|language=es-US|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best New Artist\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|Best Album\n|''[[Spoiler (album)|Spoiler]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Song\n|\"[[Presiento]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Music Video\n|\"[[Tel\u00e9fono]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|Premios Dial\n|Best Artist\n|Herself\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cadenadial.com/2020/premios-dial-ganadores-actuaciones-y-premios-especiales-182692.html|title=Premios Dial \u00a1ganadores, actuaciones y premios especiales!|date=2020-02-26|website=Cadena Dial|language=es-ES|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n* {{Twitter|Aitanax}}\n* {{Instagram|Aitanax}}\n* {{IMDb name|9380750}}\n* {{YouTube|channel=UCI505QHIvSgj8lbHY7ygE1A}}\n\n{{Aitana (singer)|state=collapsed}}\n{{Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aitana}}\n[[Category:Singers from Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Spanish female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Spanish female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Operaci\u00f3n Triunfo contestants]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Group artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Juditrojas", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aitana_(singer)"}
{"title_page": "Cheran (director)", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian film director and actor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Cheran\n| native_name        = \n| image              = Cheran (Tamil film director).jpg\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = india\n| birth_name         = Cheran Pandian\n| occupation         = film director, film producer, actor\n| parents            = Pandian, Kamala\n| years active       = 1997\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Cheran''' is an Indian film director and actor known for his works in [[Tamil cinema]]. He is a three time [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] winner for ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' (2000), ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]'' (2004) and ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005). He has also won five [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]] and six [[Filmfare Awards South|South Filmfare Awards]].\n\nCheran initially made a breakthrough as a director by making village-based drama films focusing on human relationships, and achieved critical acclaim for his work in ''[[Bharathi Kannamma]]'' (1997) and ''[[Porkkaalam]]'' (1997). He later moved on to work on themes exploring how globalisation affects the Indian middle class, and told the story of scam job offers in ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' (2000) and village-to-city emigration in ''[[Pandavar Bhoomi]]'' (2001).<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20030629114205/http://www.chennaionline.com/entertainment/filmplus/cheran.asp</ref> His most renowned film till date, ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]'' (2004), is a semi-autobiographical tale of a man at four stage of his life. He later also experienced success with the family drama film ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005) and as an actor in films such as ''[[Pirivom Santhippom]]'' (2008) and ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' (2011).\n\n== Early life ==\nCheran was born in Pazhaiyurpatty village near Madurai. His father Pandian was a film projector operator in [[Vellalur]]'s touring theatre. His mother Kamala was a primary school teacher, and he has two sisters.\n\nHe came to Chennai to pursue a career in films, and was keen to become an actor. Initially, he started career as a production manager in some films. In the film ''[[Puriyaadha Pudhir]]'' (1990), he worked as an assistant director [[K. S. Ravikumar]], and was later promoted to an associate director from ''[[Cheran Pandiyan]]'' (1992) to ''[[Nattamai]]'' (1994).\n\n== Career ==\n=== 1997\u20132003: Breakthrough and early success ===\nCheran made his directorial debut through ''[[Bharathi Kannamma]]'' (1997), a village drama narrating the relationship between the daughter of a rich family and their retainer, starring [[R. Parthiepan|Parthiban]] and [[Meena (actress)|Meena]] in the lead roles. During its release, the film ran into trouble as Thevar community who almost imposed a ban of the film due to its content. However the film won good reviews and performed well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |date=1998 |title=Mandal and movies |url=https://archive.org/details/dli.bengal.10689.21002/page/n637 |magazine=Sunday |pages=55\u201357}}</ref> In spite of controversies, the film became successful at box-office.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/2003/12/28/stories/2003122800731400.htm |title=The politics of art |last=Nambath |first=Suresh |date=28 December 2003 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=4 May 2019}}</ref> His second film, ''[[Porkkaalam]]'' (1997) was in the same genre, and also performed well commercially as well as winning favourable reviews from critics. The film, which explored the life of a hard-working potter and his poor family, earned Cheran an award for best director from the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Director|Tamil Nadu State]].\n\nUnlike his first two films, his third film did not fare well at the box office despite winning positive reviews.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jun/23che.htm</ref> ''[[Desiya Geetham]]'' (1998) told the story of a Chief Minister being kidnapped and taken to a remote village, and it subsequently met with a controversial response from politicians. Despite Cheran's intervention and explanation of the script to senior political figures, the film was quickly removed from cinema halls, much to the director's dismay.<ref>https://archive.is/20120709043545/http://chandrag.tripod.com/nov98/</ref> However, the film won good reviews and a critic noted it was \"a rare, good movie with a message\" and added that Cheran \"deserves credit for making a movie that tries to tell something and keeping away from the usual, commercial add-ons\".<ref>http://www.bbthots.com/reviews/1999/dgeetham.html</ref><ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/review.htm</ref> Following the film's failure, Cheran announced several projects before opting not to continue with them. He initially considered making another film with [[Murali (Tamil actor)|Murali]] and [[Shammi Kapoor]] titled ''Paraseega Mannan'', but the film did not progress.<ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/gcnapril.htm</ref> Cheran then moved on make an urban love story titled ''Inniya Kaadalargale'' starring [[Prashanth (actor)|Prashanth]], Shivani and himself in the lead roles, but the film was also later dropped.<ref>http://chandrag.tripod.com/jan99/</ref> Another light-hearted film was planned with [[Arun Vijay|Arunkumar]], [[Suriya]] and [[Raju Sundaram]], but it did not start production.<ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/rangan.htm</ref>\n\nHe later worked again with Parthiban and Murali for the social comedy drama, ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' (2000), which focused on scams committed by agents who promised lavish jobs and salaries abroad, and in the process swindling the money of innocent people. The film won critical acclaim upon release, and Cheran won a [[National Film Award for Best Film on Other Social Issues|National Film Award]] for his work in the film.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#4</ref> Cheran then made ''[[Pandavar Bhoomi]]'' (2001) with actors [[Arun Vijay|Arunkumar]] and [[Rajkiran]], which explored themes of wholesale emigration of villagers to the city and the loss of good, solid agricultural lands, culture and solidarity.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#5</ref> The film performed well at the box office and garnered mixed reviews from critics. A reviewer from Sify.com stated the film was \"typical overdose of Cheran melodrama masala\".<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/pandavar-bhoomi-review--pclulBgcjfigc.html</ref> Cheran then turned actor in director [[Thangar Bachan]]'s romantic drama film ''[[Solla Marandha Kadhai]]'' (2002). The film garnered mixed review but performed well at the box office.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/solla-marantha-kathai-review-tamil-pcluw5aeghgbd.html</ref>\n\n=== 2003\u20132006: ''Autograph'' and national recognition ===\nCheran first began work on ''Autograph'' in 2001 with [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]], though the actor later opted out as a result of schedule clashes.<ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/may2001.html</ref> In early 2002, Cheran announced that he was going to instead make a film titled ''Pokkisham'' and [[Kanika (actress)|Kanika]] would star alongside him. However he failed to find a financier and moved back to making ''Autograph''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nilacharal.com/enter/cinebit/c97.html|title=Nilacharal&nbsp;\u2013 A Tamil entertainment ezine presenting interesting contents and useful services|publisher=}}</ref> As producers were unwilling to finance the film, Cheran opted to produce and star in the film himself and the film consequently took over a year to make. ''Autograph'' told the story of a man named Senthil, presented in four stages of his life&nbsp;\u2013 at school, college, work and during his marriage, and Cheran called the film \"semi-autobiographical\".<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">http://www.sify.com/movies/malayalam/interview.php?id=13429274&cid=2408</ref> The film starred him alongside [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]], [[Gopika]], [[Mallika (actress)|Mallika]] and Kanika, and had a popular soundtrack composed by [[Bharathwaj]]. Four different cinematographers worked on the film; [[Ravi Varman]] had shot the school episode in Senthil's early life with a 35&nbsp;mm lens, [[Vijay Milton]] shot the Kerala scenes, Dwaraknath shot the Chennai episode with a steady cam and Shanky Mahendran shot the \"'live' part\" of the film when the camera uses the [[Point of view shot|point of view]] of Senthil's character.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" />\n\nMade at a budget of \u20b92 crore rupees, the film garnered over \u20b910 crores at the box office and became one of the most profitable Tamil films of the year. The film benefited from positive word-of-mouth and Cheran subsequently increased the number of prints from sixty five to eighty five for the second week, a rarity in Tamil cinema.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" /><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/year-2004-a-flashback/article28578111.ece</ref> The film won positive reviews from film critics, with [[Sify]].com writing that \"Cheran has used all his artists to perfection to make this love story with polish and panache\".<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/autograph-review--pclv0vfgdgghh.html</ref> Dennis Harvey of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote it was a \"well-mounted production has too much familiar melodrama, and few real highlights (notably one delightful homage to \u201970s Tamil musicals), but remains an easy watch\".<ref>https://variety.com/2004/film/reviews/autograph-2-1200531283/</ref> For the film, Cheran won a [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment|National Award for Best Popular Film]], along with two [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] and two [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]], for Best Film and Best Director.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/cheran-and-awards-news-tamil-kkfvbgifchhsi.html</ref> The film became renowned as a \"cult classic\" and spawned several other inspirations and remakes in the Indian film industry.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#6</ref>\n\nCheran then restarted work ''Pokkisham'' in 2004 but postponed the film after falling out with the new lead actress [[Meera Jasmine]]. He then the drama film ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005) focused on family relationships and Tamil culture, and cast himself in the lead role, alongside [[Rajkiran]], [[Saranya Ponvannan|Saranya]] and [[Padmapriya Janakiraman|Padmapriya]]. During production, the film went over budget and took nearly 145 days of shoot in Karaikudi, Madurai and Chennai. The film was made at a budget of \u20b92 crore rupees, and went on to make profits for the producers.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=14045327&cid=2408</ref> The film also won positive reviews, with a critic from Sify.com noting that \"Cheran has kept the flag of uncompromised cinema flying and is one of the handful of directors, whose calling card remain his artistry over the medium\", adding that the film is \"brilliant and appeals as much to the mind as the heart\".<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/thavamai-thavamirundhu-review-tamil-pclvObfhagcjb.html</ref> Upon release, the film won several awards including the [[National Film Award for Best Film on Family Welfare|another National Award]] for best film on family welfare.<ref>http://dff.nic.in/2011/53rd_nff_2006.pdf</ref>\n\n=== 2007\u20132013: Focus on acting assignments ===\nHe restarted work on ''Pokkisham'' for the third time in December 2005, after completing ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005), and approached [[Sandhya (actress)|Sandhya]] to play the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamilguardian.com/article.asp?articleid%3D389 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-11-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160422133146/http://tamilguardian.com/article.asp?articleid=389 |archivedate=22 April 2016  }}</ref> The film did not take off so he moved on to make ''[[Maya Kannadi]]'' (2007) starring himself and [[Navya Nair]] in the lead roles. ''Mayakannadi'' was based on the concept of middle class dreams turning sour due to lack of commitment and created attention prior to release owing to Cheran's recent success. However, the film fared poorly at the box office and lost money for distributors.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/may-07-01/03-05-07-maayakannadi.html</ref> It received mixed reviews and a critic noted \"after seeing the film, we hope that the director applies this message in his life by sticking to his core strength of direction rather than dabble in roles that just do not suit him\".<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#8</ref> Another reviewer from Rediff.com stated it was a \"brave, real film\" and that \"Cheran has done a superb job directing as well as acting\".<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/apr/16ssmaya.htm</ref> After the film's release, Cheran suggested that he regretted not thinking about letting someone else play the lead role instead of himself.<ref>https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:BijMP9VxalAJ:https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/cheran-on-directing-thirumanam/article26365860.ece+&cd=5&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk</ref>\n\nCheran subsequently chose to prioritise acting commitments in order to raise finances for his subsequent film. He starred in [[T. V. Chandran]]'s award-winning ''[[Aadum Koothu]]'' (2008), [[Karu Pazhaniappan]]'s ''[[Pirivom Santhippom]]'' (2008) and ''[[Raman Thediya Seethai (2008 film)|Raman Thediya Seethai]]'' (2009). In his films, he often portrayed meek and mellow roles as a family-orientated man. The films all performed well commercially, and won good reviews for Cheran as an actor.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/sep/19ssr.htm</ref><ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/raman-thediya-seethai-review.html</ref> For the fourth time, Cheran finally moved on to make ''Pokkisham'' (2009) and cast [[Padmapriya Janakiraman|Padmapriya]] alongside himself in the lead role during 2008. Set in the 1970s, the story revolved around two lovers&nbsp;\u2013 a Muslim Tamil literature student and a Hindu marine engineer working in Calcutta. ''Pokkisham'' opened to mixed reviews from critics, with many reviewers calling the screenplay too slow. The film subsequently fared poorly at the box office.<ref>http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/aug/21/slide-show-1-south-cheran-on-pokkisham.htm#1</ref>\n\nFollowing the commercial failure of ''Pokkisham'', Cheran actively chose to prioritise acting commitments. He appeared in [[Mysskin]]'s thriller ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' as a detective agent, and in Rajan Madhav's mystery drama ''[[Muran (film)|Muran]]'' during 2011. In 2013, he featured in [[Vasanth]]'s ''[[Moondru Per Moondru Kaadhal]]'' and in the anthology film ''[[Chennaiyil Oru Naal]]''. In general, all four films won positive reviews from critics and performed well commercially.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-yuddham-sei/20110204.htm</ref><ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/thriller-yudham-sei-is-value-for-money-tamil-movie-review-news-national-lcgtEfadiifsi.html</ref><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/chen-cinema/life-comes-full-circle/article4636636.ece</ref>\n\n=== 2014\u2014present: Career decline ===\nFollowing successive failures as a director, Cheran had trouble attracting producers for his next directorial projects. He also revealed his intentions of making bigger budget films to cater to modern audiences and expressed that village-based films would be difficult, as the setting had changed considerably since the start of his career. He subsequently launched a film titled ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' in 2013 starring [[Sharwanand]] and [[Nithya Menen]] in the lead roles. However, the film languished in development hell and later had a straight-to-DVD release via Cheran's C2H platform.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/jk-ennum-nanbanin-vazhkai-review-tamil-pdhs4giheeghd.html</ref><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/audio-beat-jk-ennum-nanbanin-vazhkai-a-slice-of-life/article5228673.ece</ref> The period marked a difficult stage for the director, with the lack of directing and acting offers, complemented by family trouble, financial problems owing to C2H, and negative press for controversial statements.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle.com\">https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/270816/director-cheran-hit-by-diaspora.html</ref>\n\nAfter an extended break, Cheran made a return to direction with the family drama ''[[Thirumanam (2019 film)|Thirumanam]]'' (2019) starring himself alongside [[Sukanya (actress)|Sukanya]], Umapathi Ramaiah and Kavya Shetty. The film focused on marriage between young people, and Cheran suggested that the film would urge the youth to consider some of the societal factors before entering into wedlock.<ref name=\"thehindu.com\">https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/cheran-on-directing-thirumanam/article26365860.ece</ref> The film opened to negative reviews, and fared poorly at the box office. A critic noted \"the basic problem with ''Thirumanam'' is the preachy tone of the film\" and that \"Cheran uses lengthy dialogues and songs to convey his thoughts, which often tests our patience\", concluding that the film \"is certainly not for audiences who like modern dramas\".<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/thirumanam-review-preachy-and-tiresome-review-tamil-tdbjC2hijaaif.html</ref><ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/thirumanam-movie-review-rating-cheran-5606816/</ref><ref>https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/after-underwhelming-performance-cheran-s-thirumanam-to-re-release-1490161-2019-03-30</ref>\n\n== Other ventures ==\n=== Cinema2Home ===\nIn 2014, Cheran founded a new cinema distribution platform known as \"C2H\" (Cinema2Home) in an attempt to curb out copyright infringement in the Tamil film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/cherans-idea-to-bring-the-movies-home/article6204850.ece|title=Cheran\u2019s idea to bring the movies home|date=13 July 2014|publisher=|via=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/C2H-set-to-invade-your-drawing-room/articleshow/45942037.cms|title=C2H set to invade your drawing room&nbsp;\u2013 Times of India|publisher=}}</ref> He also launched his own music company 'Dream Sounds' in 2013, which released the soundtrack album of ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' (2015) and ''[[Thirumanam]]'' (2019). C2H was expected to deliver official original DVDs on the day of a film's theatrical release to homes, for which C2H signed an agreement with DVD maker [[Moser Baer]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/in-a-first-same-day-release-in-theatres-and-on-dvd/article6742514.ece|title=In a first, same day release in theatres and on DVD|first=R.|last=Ravikumar|date=31 December 2014|publisher=}}</ref> Around 150 distributors and 3000 dealers were said to be involved in the process of bringing the DVDs to households across Tamil Nadu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Cheran-Alleges-Threats-to-C2H-Dealers/2015/01/02/article2599660.ece|title=Cheran Alleges Threats to C2H Dealers|publisher=}}</ref> He had chosen to launch the platform after his film ''JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai'' failed to attract distributors for a theatrical release and intended on it becoming the first film of the platform. He later convinced producers who were struggling to find distributors to also put their films forward for a C2H release. Other films which joined included Thangasamy's ''[[Ettuthikkum Madhayaanai]]'', [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]]'s ''[[Appavin Meesai]]'', Parthi Bhaskar's ''[[Arjunan Kadhali]]'', Sashidharan's ''[[Vaaraayo Vennilaave]]'', Mahesh Periyasamy's ''Hockey'' and Balan's ''Koditta Idangalai Nirappuga''. Films such as Kandeepan's ''[[Aavi Kumar]]'' were briefly attached to C2H before opting out.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/kochi/2015/jan/20/Now-Watch-the-Release-of-Tamil-Films-from-Your-Home-707367.html</ref>\n\nIn March 2015, Cheran released his own film ''JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai'' through the platform and opted against giving the film a theatrical release.<ref name=\"auto\" /><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/cheran-launches-c2h-with-his-movies-release/article6968179.ece</ref> The C2H initiative was later dropped as the platform did not garner support, and the remainder of the films except ''Ettuthikkum Madhayaanai'' remain unreleased.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/were-still-making-films-on-caste-shows-that-society-remains-the-same-cheran/articleshow/67806811.cms</ref><ref name=\"thehindu.com\"/> An arrest warrant was issued by a court against Cheran and his daughter Nivedha, after he did not respond to a bounced cheque following the failure of the venture in March 2016.<ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/arrest-warrant-against-director-cheran-cheque-bounce-case-40146</ref><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Cheran-daughter-appear-in-court/article16071659.ece</ref>\n\n=== Writing ===\nCheran shared his life experiences and was published as a serial article in the Tamil Weekly Magazine [[Ananda Vikatan]]. Later, it was published as a book titled ''Touring Talkies'', {{ISBN|81-89780-18-2}}. He later turned publisher with the Tamil novel ''Porum Valiyum'' (War & Pain), a novel on an emotional account of a war-torn Sri Lanka by author Savitri Advithanandhan. As a first step, he launched the publishing house \"Cheran Noolagam\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kollytalk.com/cinenews/cheran-launches-publishing-house-cheran-noolagam-79266.html|title=Cheran launches publishing house Cheran Noolagam&nbsp;\u2013 KOLLY TALK|first=|last=admin|date=18 January 2013|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n=== Bigg Boss ===\nIn 2019, Cheran entered the ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil 3|third season]]'' of the popular reality show ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil]]''. He got evicted after 90 days. He also received the \"Most Disciplined\" housemate award from Kamal Hasan.\n\n== Controversies ==\nCheran has often had a difficult relationship with producers and has made controversial statements, which have elicited discussion. In 2008, during the audio release of ''Raman Thediya Seethai'', he made a derogatory statement against press for writing rumours about him.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/july-08-05/cheran-31-07-08.html</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Cheran-lashes-at-media-apologises/articleshow/3306694.cms</ref> In 2013, he held a press conference asking parents to strictly oppose love marriages, despite having written many love stories in films. The conversation arose when he appealed to the media for assistance after his daughter had briefly run away from home with her boyfriend.<ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/cherans-daughter-says-she-wants-to-live-with-boyfriends-mother/article4993038.ece</ref>\n\nIn late 2015, prior to the [[Nadigar Sangam]] elections, Cheran publicly criticised the leadership potential and acting ability of actors [[Vishal (actor)|Vishal]] and [[Karthi]].<ref>https://silverscreen.in/news/cheran-justifies-pre-election-criticism-of-vishal-and-karthi/</ref> Cheran criticised actor [[Sharwanand]] in July 2016 for not cooperating with the promotion of ''Rajathi Raja'', the Telugu version of ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' (2016). In return, Sharwanand stated that Cheran was in the wrong, was sour because of the failure of the Tamil film and had failed to pay him his salary.<ref>https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/tollywood/050716/silly-row-over-rajadhi-raja.html</ref> In 2016, Cheran blamed Sri Lankan Tamils for being the cause of video piracy in the Tamil film industry and expressed his regret for his support of their political independence movement. His remarks were met with outrage from the Tamil diaspora.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle.com\"/>\n\nIn March 2017, Cheran launched another scathing attack against Vishal and produced a seven-page letter accusing the actor of being \"selfish, power hungry and insensitive\". In his letter, Cheran also criticised Vishal for not lending him support during the failed C2H venture. Vishal later suggested that he respected but felt pity for Cheran for his false allegations.<ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/i-respect-him-but-his-claims-make-me-pity-him-vishal-responds-to-cherans-allegations-4969208/</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/vishal-selfish-power-hungry-and-insensitive-director-cheran-lashes-out-58541</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nCheran is married to Selvarani and has two daughters, Nivedha Priyadarshini and Damini.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/cheran-meets-media-breaks-down-news-tamil-nifkrCdjjihsi.html</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Im-heartbroken-Cheran/articleshow/21649964.cms</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Family-drama-ends-daughter-agrees-to-go-with-Cheran/articleshow/21968492.cms</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-want-Damini-to-take-some-time-for-herself-Cheran/articleshow/22118558.cms</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n;Films\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Year\n! rowspan=2 | Title\n! rowspan=2 | Role\n! colspan=4 | Credited as\n! rowspan=2 class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n! width=65 | Director\n! width=65 | Actor\n! width=65 | Writer\n! width=65 | Producer\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1997 ||''[[Bharathi Kannamma]]'' ||  ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Porkkaalam]]'' || Still photographer || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"|  ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[Desiya Geetham]]'' ||  ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| 2000 || ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' ||  ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Pandavar Bhoomi]]'' ||  ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| 2002 || ''[[Solla Marandha Kadhai]]'' || Sivadhanu ||   ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}}||  || ||\n|-\n| 2004 ||  ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''|| Senthil || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' || Ramalingam Muthaiah || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Azhagai Irukkirai Bayamai Irukkirathu]]'' ||  ||   ||   ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2007 || ''[[Maya Kannadi]]'' || Kumar || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Aadum Koothu]]'' || Gnanasekaran ||   ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2008 || ''[[Pirivom Santhippom]]'' || Nadesan ||   ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Raman Thediya Seethai (2008 film)|Raman Thediya Seethai]]'' || Venugopal ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || ||\n|-\n||2009 || ''[[Pokkisham]]'' || Lenin || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2011 || ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' || J. Krishnamoorthi ||   ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Muran (film)|Muran]]'' || Nanda ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2013 || ''[[Chennaiyil Oru Naal]]'' || Satyamoorthy ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Moondru Per Moondru Kaadhal]]'' || Gunasekar ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || ||\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Kathai Thiraikathai Vasanam Iyakkam]]'' || Himself ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' ||  || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || Lyricist\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai|Rajadhi Raja]]'' ||  || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || Telugu film\n|-\n|2019 || ''[[Thirumanam (2019 film)|Thirumanam]]'' ||  Arivudainambi || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} || ||\n|-\n|2019 || ''[[Miga Miga Avasaram]]'' || || || || || || Lyricist<ref>https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/070917/cheran-turns-lyricist.html</ref>\n|-\n|2020 || ''[[Rajavukku Check]]'' || Raja ||   || style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{y}} ||  || || \n|}\n\n;Television\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! Year !! Programme / Show !! Role !! Channel !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil 3]]'' || Contestant||[[Vijay TV]] || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] || Evicted Day 91\n|}\n\n== Awards and honours ==\n=== National Film Awards ===\n* 2000&nbsp;\u2013 [[National Film Award for Best Film on Other Social Issues]] for ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]''\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment]] for ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n* 2005&nbsp;\u2013 [[National Film Award for Best Film on Family Welfare]] for ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]''\n* 2005&nbsp;\u2013 [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Tamil]] for ''[[Aadum Koothu]]''\n\n=== Tamil Nadu State Film Awards ===\n* 1997&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Director]] for ''[[Porkaalam]]''\n* 2000&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Dialogue Writer]] for ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]''\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Film]] for ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Director]] for ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n* 2005&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Film]] for ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]''\n* 2009&nbsp;\u2013 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Story Writer]] for ''[[Pokkisham]]''\n\n=== Filmfare Awards ===\n* 1997&nbsp;\u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil]] for ''[[Bharathi Kannamma]]''\n* 1998&nbsp;\u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil]] for ''[[Desiya Geetham]]''\n* 2001&nbsp;\u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil]] for ''[[Pandavar Bhoomi]]''\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil]] for ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Film&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil]] for ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n\n=== Other awards ===\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 Dinakaran-Medimix Awards for Best Film&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n* 2004&nbsp;\u2013 Dinakaran-Medimix Awards for Best Director&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]''\n* 2005&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil Nadu progressive writers association awards for Best Writer and Director&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]''\n* 2011&nbsp;\u2013 Jaya TV Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Yuddham Sei]]''\n* 2011&nbsp;- Norway international Tamil film festival awards&nbsp;- ''Kalaichigaram Award''\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Cheran}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.directorcheran.com}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0155741|name=Cheran}}\n\n{{Cheran (director)}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestTamilDirector}}\n{{TamilNaduStateAwardForBestDirector}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cheran}}\n[[Category:Male actors from Madurai]]\n[[Category:Tamil male actors]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language film directors]]\n[[Category:Tamil screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu State Film Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Kalaimamani Award]]\n[[Category:Tamil film directors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian film directors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian film directors]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Film directors from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Producers who won the Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Directors who won the Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Directors who won the Best Film on Family Welfare National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Directors who won the Best Film on Other Social Issues National Film Award]]\n[[Category:Tamil actors]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Bigg Boss contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian film director and actor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Cheran\n| native_name        = \n| image              = Cheran (Tamil film director).jpg\n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = United States of America\n| birth_name         = Cheran Pandian\n| occupation         = film director, film producer, actor\n| parents            = Pandian, Kamala\n| years active       = 1997\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Cheran''' is an Indian film director and actor known for his works in [[Tamil cinema]]. He is a three time [[National Film Awards|National Film Award]] winner for ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' (2000), ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]'' (2004) and ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005). He has also won five [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]] and six [[Filmfare Awards South|South Filmfare Awards]].\n\nCheran initially made a breakthrough as a director by making village-based drama films focusing on human relationships, and achieved critical acclaim for his work in ''[[Bharathi Kannamma]]'' (1997) and ''[[Porkkaalam]]'' (1997). He later moved on to work on themes exploring how globalisation affects the Indian middle class, and told the story of scam job offers in ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' (2000) and village-to-city emigration in ''[[Pandavar Bhoomi]]'' (2001).<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20030629114205/http://www.chennaionline.com/entertainment/filmplus/cheran.asp</ref> His most renowned film till date, ''[[Autograph (2004 film)|Autograph]]'' (2004), is a semi-autobiographical tale of a man at four stage of his life. He later also experienced success with the family drama film ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005) and as an actor in films such as ''[[Pirivom Santhippom]]'' (2008) and ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' (2011).\n\n== Early life ==\nCheran was born in Pazhaiyurpatty village near Madurai. His father Pandian was a film projector operator in [[Vellalur]]'s touring theatre. His mother Kamala was a primary school teacher, and he has two sisters.\n\nHe came to Chennai to pursue a career in films, and was keen to become an actor. Initially, he started career as a production manager in some films. In the film ''[[Puriyaadha Pudhir]]'' (1990), he worked as an assistant director [[K. S. Ravikumar]], and was later promoted to an associate director from ''[[Cheran Pandiyan]]'' (1992) to ''[[Nattamai]]'' (1994).\n\n== Career ==\n=== 1997\u20132003: Breakthrough and early success ===\nCheran made his directorial debut through ''[[Bharathi Kannamma]]'' (1997), a village drama narrating the relationship between the daughter of a rich family and their retainer, starring [[R. Parthiepan|Parthiban]] and [[Meena (actress)|Meena]] in the lead roles. During its release, the film ran into trouble as Thevar community who almost imposed a ban of the film due to its content. However the film won good reviews and performed well at the box office.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |date=1998 |title=Mandal and movies |url=https://archive.org/details/dli.bengal.10689.21002/page/n637 |magazine=Sunday |pages=55\u201357}}</ref> In spite of controversies, the film became successful at box-office.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/2003/12/28/stories/2003122800731400.htm |title=The politics of art |last=Nambath |first=Suresh |date=28 December 2003 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=4 May 2019}}</ref> His second film, ''[[Porkkaalam]]'' (1997) was in the same genre, and also performed well commercially as well as winning favourable reviews from critics. The film, which explored the life of a hard-working potter and his poor family, earned Cheran an award for best director from the [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Director|Tamil Nadu State]].\n\nUnlike his first two films, his third film did not fare well at the box office despite winning positive reviews.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jun/23che.htm</ref> ''[[Desiya Geetham]]'' (1998) told the story of a Chief Minister being kidnapped and taken to a remote village, and it subsequently met with a controversial response from politicians. Despite Cheran's intervention and explanation of the script to senior political figures, the film was quickly removed from cinema halls, much to the director's dismay.<ref>https://archive.is/20120709043545/http://chandrag.tripod.com/nov98/</ref> However, the film won good reviews and a critic noted it was \"a rare, good movie with a message\" and added that Cheran \"deserves credit for making a movie that tries to tell something and keeping away from the usual, commercial add-ons\".<ref>http://www.bbthots.com/reviews/1999/dgeetham.html</ref><ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/review.htm</ref> Following the film's failure, Cheran announced several projects before opting not to continue with them. He initially considered making another film with [[Murali (Tamil actor)|Murali]] and [[Shammi Kapoor]] titled ''Paraseega Mannan'', but the film did not progress.<ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/gcnapril.htm</ref> Cheran then moved on make an urban love story titled ''Inniya Kaadalargale'' starring [[Prashanth (actor)|Prashanth]], Shivani and himself in the lead roles, but the film was also later dropped.<ref>http://chandrag.tripod.com/jan99/</ref> Another light-hearted film was planned with [[Arun Vijay|Arunkumar]], [[Suriya]] and [[Raju Sundaram]], but it did not start production.<ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/rangan.htm</ref>\n\nHe later worked again with Parthiban and Murali for the social comedy drama, ''[[Vetri Kodi Kattu]]'' (2000), which focused on scams committed by agents who promised lavish jobs and salaries abroad, and in the process swindling the money of innocent people. The film won critical acclaim upon release, and Cheran won a [[National Film Award for Best Film on Other Social Issues|National Film Award]] for his work in the film.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#4</ref> Cheran then made ''[[Pandavar Bhoomi]]'' (2001) with actors [[Arun Vijay|Arunkumar]] and [[Rajkiran]], which explored themes of wholesale emigration of villagers to the city and the loss of good, solid agricultural lands, culture and solidarity.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#5</ref> The film performed well at the box office and garnered mixed reviews from critics. A reviewer from Sify.com stated the film was \"typical overdose of Cheran melodrama masala\".<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/pandavar-bhoomi-review--pclulBgcjfigc.html</ref> Cheran then turned actor in director [[Thangar Bachan]]'s romantic drama film ''[[Solla Marandha Kadhai]]'' (2002). The film garnered mixed review but performed well at the box office.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/solla-marantha-kathai-review-tamil-pcluw5aeghgbd.html</ref>\n\n=== 2003\u20132006: ''Autograph'' and national recognition ===\nCheran first began work on ''Autograph'' in 2001 with [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]], though the actor later opted out as a result of schedule clashes.<ref>http://www.oocities.org/hollywood/lot/2330/may2001.html</ref> In early 2002, Cheran announced that he was going to instead make a film titled ''Pokkisham'' and [[Kanika (actress)|Kanika]] would star alongside him. However he failed to find a financier and moved back to making ''Autograph''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nilacharal.com/enter/cinebit/c97.html|title=Nilacharal&nbsp;\u2013 A Tamil entertainment ezine presenting interesting contents and useful services|publisher=}}</ref> As producers were unwilling to finance the film, Cheran opted to produce and star in the film himself and the film consequently took over a year to make. ''Autograph'' told the story of a man named Senthil, presented in four stages of his life&nbsp;\u2013 at school, college, work and during his marriage, and Cheran called the film \"semi-autobiographical\".<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">http://www.sify.com/movies/malayalam/interview.php?id=13429274&cid=2408</ref> The film starred him alongside [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]], [[Gopika]], [[Mallika (actress)|Mallika]] and Kanika, and had a popular soundtrack composed by [[Bharathwaj]]. Four different cinematographers worked on the film; [[Ravi Varman]] had shot the school episode in Senthil's early life with a 35&nbsp;mm lens, [[Vijay Milton]] shot the Kerala scenes, Dwaraknath shot the Chennai episode with a steady cam and Shanky Mahendran shot the \"'live' part\" of the film when the camera uses the [[Point of view shot|point of view]] of Senthil's character.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" />\n\nMade at a budget of \u20b92 crore rupees, the film garnered over \u20b910 crores at the box office and became one of the most profitable Tamil films of the year. The film benefited from positive word-of-mouth and Cheran subsequently increased the number of prints from sixty five to eighty five for the second week, a rarity in Tamil cinema.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" /><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/year-2004-a-flashback/article28578111.ece</ref> The film won positive reviews from film critics, with [[Sify]].com writing that \"Cheran has used all his artists to perfection to make this love story with polish and panache\".<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/autograph-review--pclv0vfgdgghh.html</ref> Dennis Harvey of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote it was a \"well-mounted production has too much familiar melodrama, and few real highlights (notably one delightful homage to \u201970s Tamil musicals), but remains an easy watch\".<ref>https://variety.com/2004/film/reviews/autograph-2-1200531283/</ref> For the film, Cheran won a [[National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment|National Award for Best Popular Film]], along with two [[Filmfare Awards South|Filmfare Awards]] and two [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]], for Best Film and Best Director.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/cheran-and-awards-news-tamil-kkfvbgifchhsi.html</ref> The film became renowned as a \"cult classic\" and spawned several other inspirations and remakes in the Indian film industry.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#6</ref>\n\nCheran then restarted work ''Pokkisham'' in 2004 but postponed the film after falling out with the new lead actress [[Meera Jasmine]]. He then the drama film ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005) focused on family relationships and Tamil culture, and cast himself in the lead role, alongside [[Rajkiran]], [[Saranya Ponvannan|Saranya]] and [[Padmapriya Janakiraman|Padmapriya]]. During production, the film went over budget and took nearly 145 days of shoot in Karaikudi, Madurai and Chennai. The film was made at a budget of \u20b92 crore rupees, and went on to make profits for the producers.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?id=14045327&cid=2408</ref> The film also won positive reviews, with a critic from Sify.com noting that \"Cheran has kept the flag of uncompromised cinema flying and is one of the handful of directors, whose calling card remain his artistry over the medium\", adding that the film is \"brilliant and appeals as much to the mind as the heart\".<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/thavamai-thavamirundhu-review-tamil-pclvObfhagcjb.html</ref> Upon release, the film won several awards including the [[National Film Award for Best Film on Family Welfare|another National Award]] for best film on family welfare.<ref>http://dff.nic.in/2011/53rd_nff_2006.pdf</ref>\n\n=== 2007\u20132013: Focus on acting assignments ===\nHe restarted work on ''Pokkisham'' for the third time in December 2005, after completing ''[[Thavamai Thavamirundhu]]'' (2005), and approached [[Sandhya (actress)|Sandhya]] to play the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamilguardian.com/article.asp?articleid%3D389 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-11-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160422133146/http://tamilguardian.com/article.asp?articleid=389 |archivedate=22 April 2016  }}</ref> The film did not take off so he moved on to make ''[[Maya Kannadi]]'' (2007) starring himself and [[Navya Nair]] in the lead roles. ''Mayakannadi'' was based on the concept of middle class dreams turning sour due to lack of commitment and created attention prior to release owing to Cheran's recent success. However, the film fared poorly at the box office and lost money for distributors.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/may-07-01/03-05-07-maayakannadi.html</ref> It received mixed reviews and a critic noted \"after seeing the film, we hope that the director applies this message in his life by sticking to his core strength of direction rather than dabble in roles that just do not suit him\".<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-cherans-treasures/20090813.htm#8</ref> Another reviewer from Rediff.com stated it was a \"brave, real film\" and that \"Cheran has done a superb job directing as well as acting\".<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/apr/16ssmaya.htm</ref> After the film's release, Cheran suggested that he regretted not thinking about letting someone else play the lead role instead of himself.<ref>https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:BijMP9VxalAJ:https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/cheran-on-directing-thirumanam/article26365860.ece+&cd=5&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk</ref>\n\nCheran subsequently chose to prioritise acting commitments in order to raise finances for his subsequent film. He starred in [[T. V. Chandran]]'s award-winning ''[[Aadum Koothu]]'' (2008), [[Karu Pazhaniappan]]'s ''[[Pirivom Santhippom]]'' (2008) and ''[[Raman Thediya Seethai (2008 film)|Raman Thediya Seethai]]'' (2009). In his films, he often portrayed meek and mellow roles as a family-orientated man. The films all performed well commercially, and won good reviews for Cheran as an actor.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/sep/19ssr.htm</ref><ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/raman-thediya-seethai-review.html</ref> For the fourth time, Cheran finally moved on to make ''Pokkisham'' (2009) and cast [[Padmapriya Janakiraman|Padmapriya]] alongside himself in the lead role during 2008. Set in the 1970s, the story revolved around two lovers&nbsp;\u2013 a Muslim Tamil literature student and a Hindu marine engineer working in Calcutta. ''Pokkisham'' opened to mixed reviews from critics, with many reviewers calling the screenplay too slow. The film subsequently fared poorly at the box office.<ref>http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2009/aug/21/slide-show-1-south-cheran-on-pokkisham.htm#1</ref>\n\nFollowing the commercial failure of ''Pokkisham'', Cheran actively chose to prioritise acting commitments. He appeared in [[Mysskin]]'s thriller ''[[Yuddham Sei]]'' as a detective agent, and in Rajan Madhav's mystery drama ''[[Muran (film)|Muran]]'' during 2011. In 2013, he featured in [[Vasanth]]'s ''[[Moondru Per Moondru Kaadhal]]'' and in the anthology film ''[[Chennaiyil Oru Naal]]''. In general, all four films won positive reviews from critics and performed well commercially.<ref>https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-yuddham-sei/20110204.htm</ref><ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/thriller-yudham-sei-is-value-for-money-tamil-movie-review-news-national-lcgtEfadiifsi.html</ref><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/chen-cinema/life-comes-full-circle/article4636636.ece</ref>\n\n=== 2014\u2014present: Career decline ===\nFollowing successive failures as a director, Cheran had trouble attracting producers for his next directorial projects. He also revealed his intentions of making bigger budget films to cater to modern audiences and expressed that village-based films would be difficult, as the setting had changed considerably since the start of his career. He subsequently launched a film titled ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' in 2013 starring [[Sharwanand]] and [[Nithya Menen]] in the lead roles. However, the film languished in development hell and later had a straight-to-DVD release via Cheran's C2H platform.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/jk-ennum-nanbanin-vazhkai-review-tamil-pdhs4giheeghd.html</ref><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-reviews/audio-beat-jk-ennum-nanbanin-vazhkai-a-slice-of-life/article5228673.ece</ref> The period marked a difficult stage for the director, with the lack of directing and acting offers, complemented by family trouble, financial problems owing to C2H, and negative press for controversial statements.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle.com\">https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/270816/director-cheran-hit-by-diaspora.html</ref>\n\nAfter an extended break, Cheran made a return to direction with the family drama ''[[Thirumanam (2019 film)|Thirumanam]]'' (2019) starring himself alongside [[Sukanya (actress)|Sukanya]], Umapathi Ramaiah and Kavya Shetty. The film focused on marriage between young people, and Cheran suggested that the film would urge the youth to consider some of the societal factors before entering into wedlock.<ref name=\"thehindu.com\">https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/cheran-on-directing-thirumanam/article26365860.ece</ref> The film opened to negative reviews, and fared poorly at the box office. A critic noted \"the basic problem with ''Thirumanam'' is the preachy tone of the film\" and that \"Cheran uses lengthy dialogues and songs to convey his thoughts, which often tests our patience\", concluding that the film \"is certainly not for audiences who like modern dramas\".<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/thirumanam-review-preachy-and-tiresome-review-tamil-tdbjC2hijaaif.html</ref><ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/thirumanam-movie-review-rating-cheran-5606816/</ref><ref>https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/after-underwhelming-performance-cheran-s-thirumanam-to-re-release-1490161-2019-03-30</ref>\n\n== Other ventures ==\n=== Cinema2Home ===\nIn 2014, Cheran founded a new cinema distribution platform known as \"C2H\" (Cinema2Home) in an attempt to curb out copyright infringement in the Tamil film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/cherans-idea-to-bring-the-movies-home/article6204850.ece|title=Cheran\u2019s idea to bring the movies home|date=13 July 2014|publisher=|via=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/C2H-set-to-invade-your-drawing-room/articleshow/45942037.cms|title=C2H set to invade your drawing room&nbsp;\u2013 Times of India|publisher=}}</ref> He also launched his own music company 'Dream Sounds' in 2013, which released the soundtrack album of ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' (2015) and ''[[Thirumanam]]'' (2019). C2H was expected to deliver official original DVDs on the day of a film's theatrical release to homes, for which C2H signed an agreement with DVD maker [[Moser Baer]].<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/in-a-first-same-day-release-in-theatres-and-on-dvd/article6742514.ece|title=In a first, same day release in theatres and on DVD|first=R.|last=Ravikumar|date=31 December 2014|publisher=}}</ref> Around 150 distributors and 3000 dealers were said to be involved in the process of bringing the DVDs to households across Tamil Nadu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/Cheran-Alleges-Threats-to-C2H-Dealers/2015/01/02/article2599660.ece|title=Cheran Alleges Threats to C2H Dealers|publisher=}}</ref> He had chosen to launch the platform after his film ''JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai'' failed to attract distributors for a theatrical release and intended on it becoming the first film of the platform. He later convinced producers who were struggling to find distributors to also put their films forward for a C2H release. Other films which joined included Thangasamy's ''[[Ettuthikkum Madhayaanai]]'', [[Rohini (actress)|Rohini]]'s ''[[Appavin Meesai]]'', Parthi Bhaskar's ''[[Arjunan Kadhali]]'', Sashidharan's ''[[Vaaraayo Vennilaave]]'', Mahesh Periyasamy's ''Hockey'' and Balan's ''Koditta Idangalai Nirappuga''. Films such as Kandeepan's ''[[Aavi Kumar]]'' were briefly attached to C2H before opting out.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/kochi/2015/jan/20/Now-Watch-the-Release-of-Tamil-Films-from-Your-Home-707367.html</ref>\n\nIn March 2015, Cheran released his own film ''JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai'' through the platform and opted against giving the film a theatrical release.<ref name=\"auto\" /><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/cheran-launches-c2h-with-his-movies-release/article6968179.ece</ref> The C2H initiative was later dropped as the platform did not garner support, and the remainder of the films except ''Ettuthikkum Madhayaanai'' remain unreleased.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/were-still-making-films-on-caste-shows-that-society-remains-the-same-cheran/articleshow/67806811.cms</ref><ref name=\"thehindu.com\"/> An arrest warrant was issued by a court against Cheran and his daughter Nivedha, after he did not respond to a bounced cheque following the failure of the venture in March 2016.<ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/arrest-warrant-against-director-cheran-cheque-bounce-case-40146</ref><ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/Cheran-daughter-appear-in-court/article16071659.ece</ref>\n\n=== Writing ===\nCheran shared his life experiences and was published as a serial article in the Tamil Weekly Magazine [[Ananda Vikatan]]. Later, it was published as a book titled ''Touring Talkies'', {{ISBN|81-89780-18-2}}. He later turned publisher with the Tamil novel ''Porum Valiyum'' (War & Pain), a novel on an emotional account of a war-torn Sri Lanka by author Savitri Advithanandhan. As a first step, he launched the publishing house \"Cheran Noolagam\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kollytalk.com/cinenews/cheran-launches-publishing-house-cheran-noolagam-79266.html|title=Cheran launches publishing house Cheran Noolagam&nbsp;\u2013 KOLLY TALK|first=|last=admin|date=18 January 2013|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n=== Bigg Boss ===\nIn 2019, Cheran entered the ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil 3|third season]]'' of the popular reality show ''[[Bigg Boss Tamil]]''. He got evicted after 90 days. He also received the \"Most Disciplined\" housemate award from Kamal Hasan.\n\n== Controversies ==\nCheran has often had a difficult relationship with producers and has made controversial statements, which have elicited discussion. In 2008, during the audio release of ''Raman Thediya Seethai'', he made a derogatory statement against press for writing rumours about him.<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/july-08-05/cheran-31-07-08.html</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Cheran-lashes-at-media-apologises/articleshow/3306694.cms</ref> In 2013, he held a press conference asking parents to strictly oppose love marriages, despite having written many love stories in films. The conversation arose when he appealed to the media for assistance after his daughter had briefly run away from home with her boyfriend.<ref>https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/cherans-daughter-says-she-wants-to-live-with-boyfriends-mother/article4993038.ece</ref>\n\nIn late 2015, prior to the [[Nadigar Sangam]] elections, Cheran publicly criticised the leadership potential and acting ability of actors [[Vishal (actor)|Vishal]] and [[Karthi]].<ref>https://silverscreen.in/news/cheran-justifies-pre-election-criticism-of-vishal-and-karthi/</ref> Cheran criticised actor [[Sharwanand]] in July 2016 for not cooperating with the promotion of ''Rajathi Raja'', the Telugu version of ''[[JK Enum Nanbanin Vaazhkai]]'' (2016). In return, Sharwanand stated that Cheran was in the wrong, was sour because of the failure of the Tamil film and had failed to pay him his salary.<ref>https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/tollywood/050716/silly-row-over-rajadhi-raja.html</ref> In 2016, Cheran blamed Sri Lankan Tamils for being the cause of video piracy in the Tamil film industry and expressed his regret for his support of their political independence movement. His remarks were met with outrage from the Tamil diaspora.<ref name=\"deccanchronicle.com\"/>\n\nIn March 2017, Cheran launched another scathing attack against Vishal and produced a seven-page letter accusing the actor of being \"selfish, power hungry and insensitive\". In his letter, Cheran also criticised Vishal for not lending him support during the failed C2H venture. Vishal later suggested that he respected but felt pity for Cheran for his false allegations.<ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/i-respect-him-but-his-claims-make-me-pity-him-vishal-responds-to-cherans-allegations-4969208/</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/vishal-selfish-power-hungry-and-insensitive-director-cheran-lashes-out-58541</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nCheran is married to Selvarani and has two daughters, Nivedha Priyadarshini and Damini.<ref>https://www.sify.com/movies/cheran-meets-media-breaks-down-news-tamil-nifkrCdjjihsi.html</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Im-heartbroken-Cheran/articleshow/21649964.cms</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Family-drama-ends-daughter-agrees-to-go-with-Cheran/articleshow/21968492.cms</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/I-want-Damini-to-take-some-time-for-herself-Cheran/articleshow/22118558.cms</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n;Films\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Year\n! rowspan=2 | Title\n! rowspan=2 | Role\n! colspan=4 | Credited as\n! rowspan=2 class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n! width=65 | Director\n! width=65 | Actor\n! width=65 | Writer\n! width=65 | Producer\n|-\n| 